56static double calc_psnr( double sqe, double size )
57{
58 double mse = sqe / (PIXEL_MAX*PIXEL_MAX * size);
59 if( mse <= 0.0000000001 ) /* Max 100dB */
60 return 100;
61
62 return -10.0 * log10( mse );
63}
64
65static double calc_ssim_db( double ssim )
66{
67 double inv_ssim = 1 - ssim;
68 if( inv_ssim <= 0.0000000001 ) /* Max 100dB */
69 return 100;
70
71 return -10.0 * log10( inv_ssim );
72}
73
74static int threadpool_wait_all( x264_t *h )
75{
76 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
77 if( h->thread[i]->b_thread_active )
78 {
79 h->thread[i]->b_thread_active = 0;
80 if( (intptr_t)x264_threadpool_wait( h->threadpool, h->thread[i] ) < 0 )
81 return -1;
82 }
83 return 0;
84}

86static void frame_dump( x264_t *h )
87{
88 FILE *f = x264_fopen( h->param.psz_dump_yuv, "r+b" );
89 if( !f )
90 return;
91
92 /* Wait for the threads to finish deblocking */
93 if( h->param.b_sliced_threads )
94 threadpool_wait_all( h );
95
96 /* Write the frame in display order */
97 int frame_size = FRAME_SIZE( h->param.i_height * h->param.i_width * SIZEOF_PIXEL );
98 if( !fseek( f, (int64_t)h->fdec->i_frame * frame_size, SEEK_SET ) )
99 {
100 for( int p = 0; p < (CHROMA444 ? 3 : 1); p++ )
101 for( int y = 0; y < h->param.i_height; y++ )
102 fwrite( &h->fdec->plane[p][y*h->fdec->i_stride[p]], SIZEOF_PIXEL, h->param.i_width, f );
103 if( CHROMA_FORMAT == CHROMA_420 || CHROMA_FORMAT == CHROMA_422 )
104 {
105 int cw = h->param.i_width>>1;
106 int ch = h->param.i_height>>CHROMA_V_SHIFT;
107 pixel *planeu = x264_malloc( 2 * (cw*ch*SIZEOF_PIXEL + 32) );
108 if( planeu )
109 {
110 pixel *planev = planeu + cw*ch + 32/SIZEOF_PIXEL;
111 h->mc.plane_copy_deinterleave( planeu, cw, planev, cw, h->fdec->plane[1], h->fdec->i_stride[1], cw, ch );
112 fwrite( planeu, 1, cw*ch*SIZEOF_PIXEL, f );
113 fwrite( planev, 1, cw*ch*SIZEOF_PIXEL, f );
114 x264_free( planeu );
115 }
116 }
117 }
118 fclose( f );
119}

121/* Fill "default" values */
122static void slice_header_init( x264_t *h, x264_slice_header_t *sh,
123 x264_sps_t *sps, x264_pps_t *pps,
124 int i_idr_pic_id, int i_frame, int i_qp )
125{
126 x264_param_t *param = &h->param;
127
128 /* First we fill all fields */
129 sh->sps = sps;
130 sh->pps = pps;
131
132 sh->i_first_mb = 0;
133 sh->i_last_mb = h->mb.i_mb_count - 1;
134 sh->i_pps_id = pps->i_id;
135
136 sh->i_frame_num = i_frame;
137
138 sh->b_mbaff = PARAM_INTERLACED;
139 sh->b_field_pic = 0; /* no field support for now */
140 sh->b_bottom_field = 0; /* not yet used */
141
142 sh->i_idr_pic_id = i_idr_pic_id;
143
144 /* poc stuff, fixed later */
145 sh->i_poc = 0;
146 sh->i_delta_poc_bottom = 0;
147 sh->i_delta_poc[0] = 0;
148 sh->i_delta_poc[1] = 0;
149
150 sh->i_redundant_pic_cnt = 0;
151
152 h->mb.b_direct_auto_write = h->param.analyse.i_direct_mv_pred == X264_DIRECT_PRED_AUTO
153 && h->param.i_bframe
154 && ( h->param.rc.b_stat_write || !h->param.rc.b_stat_read );
155
156 if( !h->mb.b_direct_auto_read && sh->i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B )
157 {
158 if( h->fref[1][0]->i_poc_l0ref0 == h->fref[0][0]->i_poc )
159 {
160 if( h->mb.b_direct_auto_write )
161 sh->b_direct_spatial_mv_pred = ( h->stat.i_direct_score[1] > h->stat.i_direct_score[0] );
162 else
163 sh->b_direct_spatial_mv_pred = ( param->analyse.i_direct_mv_pred == X264_DIRECT_PRED_SPATIAL );
164 }
165 else
166 {
167 h->mb.b_direct_auto_write = 0;
168 sh->b_direct_spatial_mv_pred = 1;
169 }
170 }
171 /* else b_direct_spatial_mv_pred was read from the 2pass statsfile */
172
173 sh->b_num_ref_idx_override = 0;
174 sh->i_num_ref_idx_l0_active = 1;
175 sh->i_num_ref_idx_l1_active = 1;
176
177 sh->b_ref_pic_list_reordering[0] = h->b_ref_reorder[0];
178 sh->b_ref_pic_list_reordering[1] = h->b_ref_reorder[1];
179
180 /* If the ref list isn't in the default order, construct reordering header */
181 for( int list = 0; list < 2; list++ )
182 {
183 if( sh->b_ref_pic_list_reordering[list] )
184 {
185 int pred_frame_num = i_frame;
186 for( int i = 0; i < h->i_ref[list]; i++ )
187 {
188 int diff = h->fref[list][i]->i_frame_num - pred_frame_num;
189 sh->ref_pic_list_order[list][i].idc = ( diff > 0 );
190 sh->ref_pic_list_order[list][i].arg = (abs(diff) - 1) & ((1 << sps->i_log2_max_frame_num) - 1);
191 pred_frame_num = h->fref[list][i]->i_frame_num;
192 }
193 }
194 }
195
196 sh->i_cabac_init_idc = param->i_cabac_init_idc;
197
198 sh->i_qp = SPEC_QP(i_qp);
199 sh->i_qp_delta = sh->i_qp - pps->i_pic_init_qp;
200 sh->b_sp_for_swidth = 0;
201 sh->i_qs_delta = 0;
202
203 int deblock_thresh = i_qp + 2 * X264_MIN(param->i_deblocking_filter_alphac0, param->i_deblocking_filter_beta);
204 /* If effective qp <= 15, deblocking would have no effect anyway */
205 if( param->b_deblocking_filter && (h->mb.b_variable_qp || 15 < deblock_thresh ) )
206 sh->i_disable_deblocking_filter_idc = param->b_sliced_threads ? 2 : 0;
207 else
208 sh->i_disable_deblocking_filter_idc = 1;
209 sh->i_alpha_c0_offset = param->i_deblocking_filter_alphac0 * 2;
210 sh->i_beta_offset = param->i_deblocking_filter_beta * 2;
211}

213static void slice_header_write( bs_t *s, x264_slice_header_t *sh, int i_nal_ref_idc )
214{
215 if( sh->b_mbaff )
216 {
217 int first_x = sh->i_first_mb % sh->sps->i_mb_width;
218 int first_y = sh->i_first_mb / sh->sps->i_mb_width;
219 assert( (first_y&1) == 0 );
220 bs_write_ue( s, (2*first_x + sh->sps->i_mb_width*(first_y&~1) + (first_y&1)) >> 1 );
221 }
222 else
223 bs_write_ue( s, sh->i_first_mb );
224
225 bs_write_ue( s, sh->i_type + 5 ); /* same type things */
226 bs_write_ue( s, sh->i_pps_id );
227 bs_write( s, sh->sps->i_log2_max_frame_num, sh->i_frame_num & ((1<<sh->sps->i_log2_max_frame_num)-1) );
228
229 if( !sh->sps->b_frame_mbs_only )
230 {
231 bs_write1( s, sh->b_field_pic );
232 if( sh->b_field_pic )
233 bs_write1( s, sh->b_bottom_field );
234 }
235
236 if( sh->i_idr_pic_id >= 0 ) /* NAL IDR */
237 bs_write_ue( s, sh->i_idr_pic_id );
238
239 if( sh->sps->i_poc_type == 0 )
240 {
241 bs_write( s, sh->sps->i_log2_max_poc_lsb, sh->i_poc & ((1<<sh->sps->i_log2_max_poc_lsb)-1) );
242 if( sh->pps->b_pic_order && !sh->b_field_pic )
243 bs_write_se( s, sh->i_delta_poc_bottom );
244 }
245
246 if( sh->pps->b_redundant_pic_cnt )
247 bs_write_ue( s, sh->i_redundant_pic_cnt );
248
249 if( sh->i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B )
250 bs_write1( s, sh->b_direct_spatial_mv_pred );
251
252 if( sh->i_type == SLICE_TYPE_P || sh->i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B )
253 {
254 bs_write1( s, sh->b_num_ref_idx_override );
255 if( sh->b_num_ref_idx_override )
256 {
257 bs_write_ue( s, sh->i_num_ref_idx_l0_active - 1 );
258 if( sh->i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B )
259 bs_write_ue( s, sh->i_num_ref_idx_l1_active - 1 );
260 }
261 }
262
263 /* ref pic list reordering */
264 if( sh->i_type != SLICE_TYPE_I )
265 {
266 bs_write1( s, sh->b_ref_pic_list_reordering[0] );
267 if( sh->b_ref_pic_list_reordering[0] )
268 {
269 for( int i = 0; i < sh->i_num_ref_idx_l0_active; i++ )
270 {
271 bs_write_ue( s, sh->ref_pic_list_order[0][i].idc );
272 bs_write_ue( s, sh->ref_pic_list_order[0][i].arg );
273 }
274 bs_write_ue( s, 3 );
275 }
276 }
277 if( sh->i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B )
278 {
279 bs_write1( s, sh->b_ref_pic_list_reordering[1] );
280 if( sh->b_ref_pic_list_reordering[1] )
281 {
282 for( int i = 0; i < sh->i_num_ref_idx_l1_active; i++ )
283 {
284 bs_write_ue( s, sh->ref_pic_list_order[1][i].idc );
285 bs_write_ue( s, sh->ref_pic_list_order[1][i].arg );
286 }
287 bs_write_ue( s, 3 );
288 }
289 }
290
291 sh->b_weighted_pred = 0;
292 if( sh->pps->b_weighted_pred && sh->i_type == SLICE_TYPE_P )
293 {
294 sh->b_weighted_pred = sh->weight[0][0].weightfn || sh->weight[0][1].weightfn || sh->weight[0][2].weightfn;
295 /* pred_weight_table() */
296 bs_write_ue( s, sh->weight[0][0].i_denom ); /* luma_log2_weight_denom */
297 if( sh->sps->i_chroma_format_idc )
298 bs_write_ue( s, sh->weight[0][1].i_denom ); /* chroma_log2_weight_denom */
299 for( int i = 0; i < sh->i_num_ref_idx_l0_active; i++ )
300 {
301 int luma_weight_l0_flag = !!sh->weight[i][0].weightfn;
302 bs_write1( s, luma_weight_l0_flag );
303 if( luma_weight_l0_flag )
304 {
305 bs_write_se( s, sh->weight[i][0].i_scale );
306 bs_write_se( s, sh->weight[i][0].i_offset );
307 }
308 if( sh->sps->i_chroma_format_idc )
309 {
310 int chroma_weight_l0_flag = sh->weight[i][1].weightfn || sh->weight[i][2].weightfn;
311 bs_write1( s, chroma_weight_l0_flag );
312 if( chroma_weight_l0_flag )
313 {
314 for( int j = 1; j < 3; j++ )
315 {
316 bs_write_se( s, sh->weight[i][j].i_scale );
317 bs_write_se( s, sh->weight[i][j].i_offset );
318 }
319 }
320 }
321 }
322 }
323 else if( sh->pps->b_weighted_bipred == 1 && sh->i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B )
324 {
325 /* TODO */
326 }
327
328 if( i_nal_ref_idc != 0 )
329 {
330 if( sh->i_idr_pic_id >= 0 )
331 {
332 bs_write1( s, 0 ); /* no output of prior pics flag */
333 bs_write1( s, 0 ); /* long term reference flag */
334 }
335 else
336 {
337 bs_write1( s, sh->i_mmco_command_count > 0 ); /* adaptive_ref_pic_marking_mode_flag */
338 if( sh->i_mmco_command_count > 0 )
339 {
340 for( int i = 0; i < sh->i_mmco_command_count; i++ )
341 {
342 bs_write_ue( s, 1 ); /* mark short term ref as unused */
343 bs_write_ue( s, sh->mmco[i].i_difference_of_pic_nums - 1 );
344 }
345 bs_write_ue( s, 0 ); /* end command list */
346 }
347 }
348 }
349
350 if( sh->pps->b_cabac && sh->i_type != SLICE_TYPE_I )
351 bs_write_ue( s, sh->i_cabac_init_idc );
352
353 bs_write_se( s, sh->i_qp_delta ); /* slice qp delta */
354
355 if( sh->pps->b_deblocking_filter_control )
356 {
357 bs_write_ue( s, sh->i_disable_deblocking_filter_idc );
358 if( sh->i_disable_deblocking_filter_idc != 1 )
359 {
360 bs_write_se( s, sh->i_alpha_c0_offset >> 1 );
361 bs_write_se( s, sh->i_beta_offset >> 1 );
362 }
363 }
364}

366/* If we are within a reasonable distance of the end of the memory allocated for the bitstream, */
367/* reallocate, adding an arbitrary amount of space. */
368static int bitstream_check_buffer_internal( x264_t *h, int size, int b_cabac, int i_nal )
369{
370 if( (b_cabac && (h->cabac.p_end - h->cabac.p < size)) ||
371 (h->out.bs.p_end - h->out.bs.p < size) )
372 {
373 if( size > INT_MAX - h->out.i_bitstream )
374 return -1;
375 int buf_size = h->out.i_bitstream + size;
376 uint8_t *buf = x264_malloc( buf_size );
377 if( !buf )
378 return -1;
379 int aligned_size = h->out.i_bitstream & ~15;
380 h->mc.memcpy_aligned( buf, h->out.p_bitstream, aligned_size );
381 memcpy( buf + aligned_size, h->out.p_bitstream + aligned_size, h->out.i_bitstream - aligned_size );
382
383 intptr_t delta = buf - h->out.p_bitstream;
384
385 h->out.bs.p_start += delta;
386 h->out.bs.p += delta;
387 h->out.bs.p_end = buf + buf_size;
388
389 h->cabac.p_start += delta;
390 h->cabac.p += delta;
391 h->cabac.p_end = buf + buf_size;
392
393 for( int i = 0; i <= i_nal; i++ )
394 h->out.nal[i].p_payload += delta;
395
396 x264_free( h->out.p_bitstream );
397 h->out.p_bitstream = buf;
398 h->out.i_bitstream = buf_size;
399 }
400 return 0;
401}
402
403static int bitstream_check_buffer( x264_t *h )
404{
405 int max_row_size = (2500 << SLICE_MBAFF) * h->mb.i_mb_width;
406 return bitstream_check_buffer_internal( h, max_row_size, h->param.b_cabac, h->out.i_nal );
407}
408
409static int bitstream_check_buffer_filler( x264_t *h, int filler )
410{
411 filler += 32; // add padding for safety
412 return bitstream_check_buffer_internal( h, filler, 0, -1 );
413}

431static int validate_parameters( x264_t *h, int b_open )
432{
433 if( !h->param.pf_log )
434 {
435 x264_log_internal( X264_LOG_ERROR, "pf_log not set! did you forget to call x264_param_default?\n" );
436 return -1;
437 }
438
439#if HAVE_MMX
440 if( b_open )
441 {
442 uint32_t cpuflags = x264_cpu_detect();
443 int fail = 0;
444#ifdef __SSE__
445 if( !(cpuflags & X264_CPU_SSE) )
446 {
447 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "your cpu does not support SSE1, but x264 was compiled with asm\n");
448 fail = 1;
449 }
450#else
451 if( !(cpuflags & X264_CPU_MMX2) )
452 {
453 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "your cpu does not support MMXEXT, but x264 was compiled with asm\n");
454 fail = 1;
455 }
456#endif
457 if( fail )
458 {
459 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "to run x264, recompile without asm (configure --disable-asm)\n");
460 return -1;
461 }
462 }
463#endif
464
465#if HAVE_INTERLACED
466 h->param.b_interlaced = !!PARAM_INTERLACED;
467#else
468 if( h->param.b_interlaced )
469 {
470 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "not compiled with interlaced support\n" );
471 return -1;
472 }
473#endif
474
475#define MAX_RESOLUTION 16384
476 if( h->param.i_width <= 0 || h->param.i_height <= 0 ||
477 h->param.i_width > MAX_RESOLUTION || h->param.i_height > MAX_RESOLUTION )
478 {
479 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "invalid width x height (%dx%d)\n",
480 h->param.i_width, h->param.i_height );
481 return -1;
482 }
483
484 int i_csp = h->param.i_csp & X264_CSP_MASK;
485#if X264_CHROMA_FORMAT
486 if( CHROMA_FORMAT != CHROMA_400 && i_csp == X264_CSP_I400 )
487 {
488 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "not compiled with 4:0:0 support\n" );
489 return -1;
490 }
491 else if( CHROMA_FORMAT != CHROMA_420 && i_csp >= X264_CSP_I420 && i_csp < X264_CSP_I422 )
492 {
493 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "not compiled with 4:2:0 support\n" );
494 return -1;
495 }
496 else if( CHROMA_FORMAT != CHROMA_422 && i_csp >= X264_CSP_I422 && i_csp < X264_CSP_I444 )
497 {
498 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "not compiled with 4:2:2 support\n" );
499 return -1;
500 }
501 else if( CHROMA_FORMAT != CHROMA_444 && i_csp >= X264_CSP_I444 && i_csp <= X264_CSP_RGB )
502 {
503 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "not compiled with 4:4:4 support\n" );
504 return -1;
505 }
506#endif
507 if( i_csp <= X264_CSP_NONE || i_csp >= X264_CSP_MAX )
508 {
509 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "invalid CSP (only I400/I420/YV12/NV12/NV21/I422/YV16/NV16/YUYV/UYVY/"
510 "I444/YV24/BGR/BGRA/RGB supported)\n" );
511 return -1;
512 }
513
514 int w_mod = 1;
515 int h_mod = 1 << (PARAM_INTERLACED || h->param.b_fake_interlaced);
516 if( i_csp == X264_CSP_I400 )
517 {
518 h->param.analyse.i_chroma_qp_offset = 0;
519 h->param.analyse.b_chroma_me = 0;
520 h->param.vui.i_colmatrix = 2; /* undefined */
521 }
522 else if( i_csp < X264_CSP_I444 )
523 {
524 w_mod = 2;
525 if( i_csp < X264_CSP_I422 )
526 h_mod *= 2;
527 }
528
529 if( h->param.i_width % w_mod )
530 {
531 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "width not divisible by %d (%dx%d)\n",
532 w_mod, h->param.i_width, h->param.i_height );
533 return -1;
534 }
535 if( h->param.i_height % h_mod )
536 {
537 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "height not divisible by %d (%dx%d)\n",
538 h_mod, h->param.i_width, h->param.i_height );
539 return -1;
540 }
541
542 if( h->param.crop_rect.i_left < 0 || h->param.crop_rect.i_left >= h->param.i_width ||
543 h->param.crop_rect.i_right < 0 || h->param.crop_rect.i_right >= h->param.i_width ||
544 h->param.crop_rect.i_top < 0 || h->param.crop_rect.i_top >= h->param.i_height ||
545 h->param.crop_rect.i_bottom < 0 || h->param.crop_rect.i_bottom >= h->param.i_height ||
546 h->param.crop_rect.i_left + h->param.crop_rect.i_right >= h->param.i_width ||
547 h->param.crop_rect.i_top + h->param.crop_rect.i_bottom >= h->param.i_height )
548 {
549 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "invalid crop-rect %d,%d,%d,%d\n", h->param.crop_rect.i_left,
550 h->param.crop_rect.i_top, h->param.crop_rect.i_right, h->param.crop_rect.i_bottom );
551 return -1;
552 }
553 if( h->param.crop_rect.i_left % w_mod || h->param.crop_rect.i_right % w_mod ||
554 h->param.crop_rect.i_top % h_mod || h->param.crop_rect.i_bottom % h_mod )
555 {
556 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "crop-rect %d,%d,%d,%d not divisible by %dx%d\n", h->param.crop_rect.i_left,
557 h->param.crop_rect.i_top, h->param.crop_rect.i_right, h->param.crop_rect.i_bottom, w_mod, h_mod );
558 return -1;
559 }
560
561 if( h->param.vui.i_sar_width <= 0 || h->param.vui.i_sar_height <= 0 )
562 {
563 h->param.vui.i_sar_width = 0;
564 h->param.vui.i_sar_height = 0;
565 }
566
567 if( h->param.i_threads == X264_THREADS_AUTO )
568 {
569 h->param.i_threads = x264_cpu_num_processors() * (h->param.b_sliced_threads?2:3)/2;
570 /* Avoid too many threads as they don't improve performance and
571 * complicate VBV. Capped at an arbitrary 2 rows per thread. */
572 int max_threads = X264_MAX( 1, (h->param.i_height+15)/16 / 2 );
573 h->param.i_threads = X264_MIN( h->param.i_threads, max_threads );
574 }
575 int max_sliced_threads = X264_MAX( 1, (h->param.i_height+15)/16 / 4 );
576 if( h->param.i_threads > 1 )
577 {
578#if !HAVE_THREAD
579 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "not compiled with thread support!\n");
580 h->param.i_threads = 1;
581#endif
582 /* Avoid absurdly small thread slices as they can reduce performance
583 * and VBV compliance. Capped at an arbitrary 4 rows per thread. */
584 if( h->param.b_sliced_threads )
585 h->param.i_threads = X264_MIN( h->param.i_threads, max_sliced_threads );
586 }
587 h->param.i_threads = x264_clip3( h->param.i_threads, 1, X264_THREAD_MAX );
588 if( h->param.i_threads == 1 )
589 {
590 h->param.b_sliced_threads = 0;
591 h->param.i_lookahead_threads = 1;
592 }
593 h->i_thread_frames = h->param.b_sliced_threads ? 1 : h->param.i_threads;
594 if( h->i_thread_frames > 1 )
595 h->param.nalu_process = NULL;
596
597 if( h->param.b_opencl )
598 {
599#if !HAVE_OPENCL
600 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "OpenCL: not compiled with OpenCL support, disabling\n" );
601 h->param.b_opencl = 0;
602#elif BIT_DEPTH > 8
603 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "OpenCL lookahead does not support high bit depth, disabling opencl\n" );
604 h->param.b_opencl = 0;
605#else
606 if( h->param.i_width < 32 || h->param.i_height < 32 )
607 {
608 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "OpenCL: frame size is too small, disabling opencl\n" );
609 h->param.b_opencl = 0;
610 }
611#endif
612 if( h->param.opencl_device_id && h->param.i_opencl_device )
613 {
614 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "OpenCL: device id and device skip count configured; dropping skip\n" );
615 h->param.i_opencl_device = 0;
616 }
617 }
618
619 h->param.i_keyint_max = x264_clip3( h->param.i_keyint_max, 1, X264_KEYINT_MAX_INFINITE );
620 if( h->param.i_keyint_max == 1 )
621 {
622 h->param.b_intra_refresh = 0;
623 h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred = 0;
624 h->param.i_frame_reference = 1;
625 h->param.i_dpb_size = 1;
626 }
627
628 if( h->param.i_frame_packing < -1 || h->param.i_frame_packing > 7 )
629 {
630 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "ignoring unknown frame packing value\n" );
631 h->param.i_frame_packing = -1;
632 }
633 if( h->param.i_frame_packing == 7 &&
634 ((h->param.i_width - h->param.crop_rect.i_left - h->param.crop_rect.i_right) % 3 ||
635 (h->param.i_height - h->param.crop_rect.i_top - h->param.crop_rect.i_bottom) % 3) )
636 {
637 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "cropped resolution %dx%d not compatible with tile format frame packing\n",
638 h->param.i_width - h->param.crop_rect.i_left - h->param.crop_rect.i_right,
639 h->param.i_height - h->param.crop_rect.i_top - h->param.crop_rect.i_bottom );
640 return -1;
641 }
642
643 if( h->param.mastering_display.b_mastering_display )
644 {
645 if( h->param.mastering_display.i_green_x > UINT16_MAX || h->param.mastering_display.i_green_x < 0 ||
646 h->param.mastering_display.i_green_y > UINT16_MAX || h->param.mastering_display.i_green_y < 0 ||
647 h->param.mastering_display.i_blue_x > UINT16_MAX || h->param.mastering_display.i_blue_x < 0 ||
648 h->param.mastering_display.i_blue_y > UINT16_MAX || h->param.mastering_display.i_blue_y < 0 ||
649 h->param.mastering_display.i_red_x > UINT16_MAX || h->param.mastering_display.i_red_x < 0 ||
650 h->param.mastering_display.i_red_y > UINT16_MAX || h->param.mastering_display.i_red_y < 0 ||
651 h->param.mastering_display.i_white_x > UINT16_MAX || h->param.mastering_display.i_white_x < 0 ||
652 h->param.mastering_display.i_white_y > UINT16_MAX || h->param.mastering_display.i_white_y < 0 )
653 {
654 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "mastering display xy coordinates out of range [0,%u]\n", UINT16_MAX );
655 return -1;
656 }
657 if( h->param.mastering_display.i_display_max > UINT32_MAX || h->param.mastering_display.i_display_max < 0 ||
658 h->param.mastering_display.i_display_min > UINT32_MAX || h->param.mastering_display.i_display_min < 0 )
659 {
660 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "mastering display brightness out of range [0,%u]\n", UINT32_MAX );
661 return -1;
662 }
663 if( h->param.mastering_display.i_display_min == 50000 && h->param.mastering_display.i_display_max == 50000 )
664 {
665 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "mastering display min and max brightness cannot both be 50000\n" );
666 return -1;
667 }
668 }
669
670 if( h->param.content_light_level.b_cll &&
671 (h->param.content_light_level.i_max_cll > UINT16_MAX || h->param.content_light_level.i_max_cll < 0 ||
672 h->param.content_light_level.i_max_fall > UINT16_MAX || h->param.content_light_level.i_max_fall < 0) )
673 {
674 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "content light levels out of range [0,%u]\n", UINT16_MAX );
675 return -1;
676 }
677
678 /* Detect default ffmpeg settings and terminate with an error. */
679 if( b_open )
680 {
681 int score = 0;
682 score += h->param.analyse.i_me_range == 0;
683 score += h->param.rc.i_qp_step == 3;
684 score += h->param.i_keyint_max == 12;
685 score += h->param.rc.i_qp_min == 2;
686 score += h->param.rc.i_qp_max == 31;
687 score += h->param.rc.f_qcompress == 0.5;
688 score += fabs(h->param.rc.f_ip_factor - 1.25) < 0.01;
689 score += fabs(h->param.rc.f_pb_factor - 1.25) < 0.01;
690 score += h->param.analyse.inter == 0 && h->param.analyse.i_subpel_refine == 8;
691 if( score >= 5 )
692 {
693 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "broken ffmpeg default settings detected\n" );
694 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "use an encoding preset (e.g. -vpre medium)\n" );
695 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "preset usage: -vpre <speed> -vpre <profile>\n" );
696 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "speed presets are listed in x264 --help\n" );
697 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "profile is optional; x264 defaults to high\n" );
698 return -1;
699 }
700 }
701
702 if( h->param.rc.i_rc_method < 0 || h->param.rc.i_rc_method > 2 )
703 {
704 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "no ratecontrol method specified\n" );
705 return -1;
706 }
707
708 if( PARAM_INTERLACED )
709 h->param.b_pic_struct = 1;
710
711 if( h->param.i_avcintra_class )
712 {
713 if( BIT_DEPTH != 10 )
714 {
715 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "%2d-bit AVC-Intra is not widely compatible\n", BIT_DEPTH );
716 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "10-bit x264 is required to encode AVC-Intra\n" );
717 return -1;
718 }
719
720 int type = h->param.i_avcintra_class == 480 ? 4 :
721 h->param.i_avcintra_class == 300 ? 3 :
722 h->param.i_avcintra_class == 200 ? 2 :
723 h->param.i_avcintra_class == 100 ? 1 :
724 h->param.i_avcintra_class == 50 ? 0 : -1;
725 if( type < 0 )
726 {
727 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "Invalid AVC-Intra class\n" );
728 return -1;
729 }
730 else if( type > 2 && h->param.i_avcintra_flavor != X264_AVCINTRA_FLAVOR_SONY )
731 {
732 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "AVC-Intra %d only supported by Sony XAVC flavor\n", h->param.i_avcintra_class );
733 return -1;
734 }

793 int res = -1;
794 if( i_csp >= X264_CSP_I420 && i_csp < X264_CSP_I422 && !type )
795 {
796 if( h->param.i_width == 1440 && h->param.i_height == 1080 ) res = 1;
797 else if( h->param.i_width == 960 && h->param.i_height == 720 ) res = 0;
798 }
799 else if( i_csp >= X264_CSP_I422 && i_csp < X264_CSP_I444 && type )
800 {
801 if( type < 3 )
802 {
803 if( h->param.i_width == 1920 && h->param.i_height == 1080 ) res = 1;
804 else if( h->param.i_width == 2048 && h->param.i_height == 1080 ) res = 1;
805 else if( h->param.i_width == 1280 && h->param.i_height == 720 ) res = 0;
806 }
807 else
808 {
809 if( h->param.i_width == 3840 && h->param.i_height == 2160 ) res = 0;
810 else if( h->param.i_width == 4096 && h->param.i_height == 2160 ) res = 0;
811 }
812 }
813 else
814 {
815 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "Invalid colorspace for AVC-Intra %d\n", h->param.i_avcintra_class );
816 return -1;
817 }
818
819 if( res < 0 )
820 {
821 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "Resolution %dx%d invalid for AVC-Intra %d\n",
822 h->param.i_width, h->param.i_height, h->param.i_avcintra_class );
823 return -1;
824 }

838 int i;
839 uint32_t fps_num = h->param.i_fps_num, fps_den = h->param.i_fps_den;
840 x264_reduce_fraction( &fps_num, &fps_den );
841 for( i = 0; i < 7; i++ )
842 {
843 if( avcintra_lut[type][res][i].fps_num == fps_num &&
844 avcintra_lut[type][res][i].fps_den == fps_den &&
845 avcintra_lut[type][res][i].interlaced == PARAM_INTERLACED )
846 {
847 break;
848 }

851 {
852 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "FPS %d/%d%c not compatible with AVC-Intra %d\n",
853 h->param.i_fps_num, h->param.i_fps_den, PARAM_INTERLACED ? 'i' : 'p', h->param.i_avcintra_class );
854 return -1;

858 h->param.b_intra_refresh = 0;

872 h->param.analyse.intra = X264_ANALYSE_I8x8;

874 h->param.b_cabac = !type;
875 h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size = avcintra_lut[type][res][i].frame_size;

877 h->param.rc.i_bitrate = h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size * fps_num / fps_den;

882 memcpy( h->param.cqm_4iy, avcintra_lut[type][res][i].cqm_4iy, sizeof(h->param.cqm_4iy) );
883 memcpy( h->param.cqm_4ic, avcintra_lut[type][res][i].cqm_4ic, sizeof(h->param.cqm_4ic) );
884 memcpy( h->param.cqm_8iy, avcintra_lut[type][res][i].cqm_8iy, sizeof(h->param.cqm_8iy) );

886 /* Sony XAVC flavor much more simple */
887 if( h->param.i_avcintra_flavor == X264_AVCINTRA_FLAVOR_SONY )
888 {
889 h->param.i_slice_count = 8;
890 if( h->param.b_sliced_threads )
891 h->param.i_threads = h->param.i_slice_count;
892 /* Sony XAVC unlike AVC-Intra doesn't seem to have a QP floor */
893 }
894 else
895 {
896 /* Need exactly 10 slices of equal MB count... why? $deity knows... */
897 h->param.i_slice_max_mbs = ((h->param.i_width + 15) / 16) * ((h->param.i_height + 15) / 16) / 10;
898 h->param.i_slice_max_size = 0;
899 /* The slice structure only allows a maximum of 2 threads for 1080i/p
900 * and 1 or 5 threads for 720p */
901 if( h->param.b_sliced_threads )
902 {
903 if( res )
904 h->param.i_threads = X264_MIN( 2, h->param.i_threads );
905 else
906 {
907 h->param.i_threads = X264_MIN( 5, h->param.i_threads );
908 if( h->param.i_threads < 5 )
909 h->param.i_threads = 1;
910 }
911 }
912
913 /* Official encoder doesn't appear to go under 13
914 * and Avid cannot handle negative QPs */
915 h->param.rc.i_qp_min = X264_MAX( h->param.rc.i_qp_min, QP_BD_OFFSET + 1 );
916 }
917
918 if( type )
919 h->param.vui.i_sar_width = h->param.vui.i_sar_height = 1;
920 else
921 {
922 h->param.vui.i_sar_width = 4;
923 h->param.vui.i_sar_height = 3;
924 }
925 }

1285 else
1286 {
1287 /* If we're using much slower lookahead settings than encoding settings, it helps a lot to use
1288 * more lookahead threads. This typically happens in the first pass of a two-pass encode, so
1289 * try to guess at this sort of case.
1290 *
1291 * Tuned by a little bit of real encoding with the various presets. */
1292 int badapt = h->param.i_bframe_adaptive == X264_B_ADAPT_TRELLIS;
1293 int subme = X264_MIN( h->param.analyse.i_subpel_refine / 3, 3 ) + (h->param.analyse.i_subpel_refine > 1);
1294 int bframes = X264_MIN( (h->param.i_bframe - 1) / 3, 3 );
1295
1296 /* [b-adapt 0/1 vs 2][quantized subme][quantized bframes] */
1297 static const uint8_t lookahead_thread_div[2][5][4] =
1298 {{{6,6,6,6}, {3,3,3,3}, {4,4,4,4}, {6,6,6,6}, {12,12,12,12}},
1299 {{3,2,1,1}, {2,1,1,1}, {4,3,2,1}, {6,4,3,2}, {12, 9, 6, 4}}};
1300
1301 h->param.i_lookahead_threads = h->param.i_threads / lookahead_thread_div[badapt][subme][bframes];
1302 /* Since too many lookahead threads significantly degrades lookahead accuracy, limit auto
1303 * lookahead threads to about 8 macroblock rows high each at worst. This number is chosen
1304 * pretty much arbitrarily. */
1305 h->param.i_lookahead_threads = X264_MIN( h->param.i_lookahead_threads, h->param.i_height / 128 );
1306 }
1307 }
1308 h->param.i_lookahead_threads = x264_clip3( h->param.i_lookahead_threads, 1, X264_MIN( max_sliced_threads, X264_LOOKAHEAD_THREAD_MAX ) );
1309
1310 if( PARAM_INTERLACED )
1311 {
1312 if( h->param.analyse.i_me_method >= X264_ME_ESA )
1313 {
1314 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "interlace + me=esa is not implemented\n" );
1315 h->param.analyse.i_me_method = X264_ME_UMH;
1316 }
1317 if( h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred > 0 )
1318 {
1319 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "interlace + weightp is not implemented\n" );
1320 h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred = X264_WEIGHTP_NONE;
1321 }
1322 }
1323
1324 if( !h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred && h->param.rc.b_mb_tree && h->param.analyse.b_psy )
1325 h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred = X264_WEIGHTP_FAKE;
1326
1327 if( h->i_thread_frames > 1 )
1328 {
1329 int r = h->param.analyse.i_mv_range_thread;
1330 int r2;
1331 if( r <= 0 )
1332 {
1333 // half of the available space is reserved and divided evenly among the threads,
1334 // the rest is allocated to whichever thread is far enough ahead to use it.
1335 // reserving more space increases quality for some videos, but costs more time
1336 // in thread synchronization.
1337 int max_range = (h->param.i_height + X264_THREAD_HEIGHT) / h->i_thread_frames - X264_THREAD_HEIGHT;
1338 r = max_range / 2;
1339 }
1340 r = X264_MAX( r, h->param.analyse.i_me_range );
1341 r = X264_MIN( r, h->param.analyse.i_mv_range );
1342 // round up to use the whole mb row
1343 r2 = (r & ~15) + ((-X264_THREAD_HEIGHT) & 15);
1344 if( r2 < r )
1345 r2 += 16;
1346 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_DEBUG, "using mv_range_thread = %d\n", r2 );
1347 h->param.analyse.i_mv_range_thread = r2;
1348 }
1349
1350 if( h->param.rc.f_rate_tolerance < 0 )
1351 h->param.rc.f_rate_tolerance = 0;
1352 if( h->param.rc.f_qblur < 0 )
1353 h->param.rc.f_qblur = 0;
1354 if( h->param.rc.f_complexity_blur < 0 )
1355 h->param.rc.f_complexity_blur = 0;
1356
1357 h->param.i_sps_id &= 31;
1358
1359 h->param.i_nal_hrd = x264_clip3( h->param.i_nal_hrd, X264_NAL_HRD_NONE, X264_NAL_HRD_CBR );
1360
1361 if( h->param.i_nal_hrd && !h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size )
1362 {
1363 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "NAL HRD parameters require VBV parameters\n" );
1364 h->param.i_nal_hrd = X264_NAL_HRD_NONE;
1365 }
1366
1367 if( h->param.i_nal_hrd == X264_NAL_HRD_CBR &&
1368 (h->param.rc.i_bitrate != h->param.rc.i_vbv_max_bitrate || !h->param.rc.i_vbv_max_bitrate) )
1369 {
1370 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "CBR HRD requires constant bitrate\n" );
1371 h->param.i_nal_hrd = X264_NAL_HRD_VBR;
1372 }
1373
1374 if( h->param.i_nal_hrd == X264_NAL_HRD_CBR )
1375 h->param.rc.b_filler = 1;
1376
1377 /* ensure the booleans are 0 or 1 so they can be used in math */
1378#define BOOLIFY(x) h->param.x = !!h->param.x
1379 BOOLIFY( b_cabac );
1380 BOOLIFY( b_constrained_intra );
1381 BOOLIFY( b_deblocking_filter );
1382 BOOLIFY( b_deterministic );
1383 BOOLIFY( b_sliced_threads );
1384 BOOLIFY( b_interlaced );
1385 BOOLIFY( b_intra_refresh );
1386 BOOLIFY( b_aud );
1387 BOOLIFY( b_repeat_headers );
1388 BOOLIFY( b_annexb );
1389 BOOLIFY( b_vfr_input );
1390 BOOLIFY( b_pulldown );
1391 BOOLIFY( b_tff );
1392 BOOLIFY( b_pic_struct );
1393 BOOLIFY( b_fake_interlaced );
1394 BOOLIFY( b_open_gop );
1395 BOOLIFY( b_bluray_compat );
1396 BOOLIFY( b_stitchable );
1397 BOOLIFY( b_full_recon );
1398 BOOLIFY( b_opencl );
1399 BOOLIFY( analyse.b_transform_8x8 );
1400 BOOLIFY( analyse.b_weighted_bipred );
1401 BOOLIFY( analyse.b_chroma_me );
1402 BOOLIFY( analyse.b_mixed_references );
1403 BOOLIFY( analyse.b_fast_pskip );
1404 BOOLIFY( analyse.b_dct_decimate );
1405 BOOLIFY( analyse.b_psy );
1406 BOOLIFY( analyse.b_psnr );
1407 BOOLIFY( analyse.b_ssim );
1408 BOOLIFY( rc.b_stat_write );
1409 BOOLIFY( rc.b_stat_read );
1410 BOOLIFY( rc.b_mb_tree );
1411 BOOLIFY( rc.b_filler );
1412#undef BOOLIFY
1413
1414 return 0;
1415}

1417static void mbcmp_init( x264_t *h )
1418{
1419 int satd = !h->mb.b_lossless && h->param.analyse.i_subpel_refine > 1;
1420 memcpy( h->pixf.mbcmp, satd ? h->pixf.satd : h->pixf.sad_aligned, sizeof(h->pixf.mbcmp) );
1421 memcpy( h->pixf.mbcmp_unaligned, satd ? h->pixf.satd : h->pixf.sad, sizeof(h->pixf.mbcmp_unaligned) );
1422 h->pixf.intra_mbcmp_x3_16x16 = satd ? h->pixf.intra_satd_x3_16x16 : h->pixf.intra_sad_x3_16x16;
1423 h->pixf.intra_mbcmp_x3_8x16c = satd ? h->pixf.intra_satd_x3_8x16c : h->pixf.intra_sad_x3_8x16c;
1424 h->pixf.intra_mbcmp_x3_8x8c = satd ? h->pixf.intra_satd_x3_8x8c : h->pixf.intra_sad_x3_8x8c;
1425 h->pixf.intra_mbcmp_x3_8x8 = satd ? h->pixf.intra_sa8d_x3_8x8 : h->pixf.intra_sad_x3_8x8;
1426 h->pixf.intra_mbcmp_x3_4x4 = satd ? h->pixf.intra_satd_x3_4x4 : h->pixf.intra_sad_x3_4x4;
1427 h->pixf.intra_mbcmp_x9_4x4 = h->param.b_cpu_independent || h->mb.b_lossless ? NULL
1428 : satd ? h->pixf.intra_satd_x9_4x4 : h->pixf.intra_sad_x9_4x4;
1429 h->pixf.intra_mbcmp_x9_8x8 = h->param.b_cpu_independent || h->mb.b_lossless ? NULL
1430 : satd ? h->pixf.intra_sa8d_x9_8x8 : h->pixf.intra_sad_x9_8x8;
1431 satd &= h->param.analyse.i_me_method == X264_ME_TESA;
1432 memcpy( h->pixf.fpelcmp, satd ? h->pixf.satd : h->pixf.sad, sizeof(h->pixf.fpelcmp) );
1433 memcpy( h->pixf.fpelcmp_x3, satd ? h->pixf.satd_x3 : h->pixf.sad_x3, sizeof(h->pixf.fpelcmp_x3) );
1434 memcpy( h->pixf.fpelcmp_x4, satd ? h->pixf.satd_x4 : h->pixf.sad_x4, sizeof(h->pixf.fpelcmp_x4) );
1435}

1437static void chroma_dsp_init( x264_t *h )
1438{
1439 memcpy( h->luma2chroma_pixel, x264_luma2chroma_pixel[CHROMA_FORMAT], sizeof(h->luma2chroma_pixel) );
1440
1441 switch( CHROMA_FORMAT )
1442 {
1443 case CHROMA_400:
1444 h->mc.prefetch_fenc = h->mc.prefetch_fenc_400;
1445 break;
1446 case CHROMA_420:
1447 memcpy( h->predict_chroma, h->predict_8x8c, sizeof(h->predict_chroma) );
1448 h->mc.prefetch_fenc = h->mc.prefetch_fenc_420;
1449 h->loopf.deblock_chroma[0] = h->loopf.deblock_h_chroma_420;
1450 h->loopf.deblock_chroma_intra[0] = h->loopf.deblock_h_chroma_420_intra;
1451 h->loopf.deblock_chroma_mbaff = h->loopf.deblock_chroma_420_mbaff;
1452 h->loopf.deblock_chroma_intra_mbaff = h->loopf.deblock_chroma_420_intra_mbaff;
1453 h->pixf.intra_mbcmp_x3_chroma = h->pixf.intra_mbcmp_x3_8x8c;
1454 h->quantf.coeff_last[DCT_CHROMA_DC] = h->quantf.coeff_last4;
1455 h->quantf.coeff_level_run[DCT_CHROMA_DC] = h->quantf.coeff_level_run4;
1456 break;
1457 case CHROMA_422:
1458 memcpy( h->predict_chroma, h->predict_8x16c, sizeof(h->predict_chroma) );
1459 h->mc.prefetch_fenc = h->mc.prefetch_fenc_422;
1460 h->loopf.deblock_chroma[0] = h->loopf.deblock_h_chroma_422;
1461 h->loopf.deblock_chroma_intra[0] = h->loopf.deblock_h_chroma_422_intra;
1462 h->loopf.deblock_chroma_mbaff = h->loopf.deblock_chroma_422_mbaff;
1463 h->loopf.deblock_chroma_intra_mbaff = h->loopf.deblock_chroma_422_intra_mbaff;
1464 h->pixf.intra_mbcmp_x3_chroma = h->pixf.intra_mbcmp_x3_8x16c;
1465 h->quantf.coeff_last[DCT_CHROMA_DC] = h->quantf.coeff_last8;
1466 h->quantf.coeff_level_run[DCT_CHROMA_DC] = h->quantf.coeff_level_run8;
1467 break;
1468 case CHROMA_444:
1469 h->mc.prefetch_fenc = h->mc.prefetch_fenc_422; /* FIXME: doesn't cover V plane */
1470 h->loopf.deblock_chroma_mbaff = h->loopf.deblock_luma_mbaff;
1471 h->loopf.deblock_chroma_intra_mbaff = h->loopf.deblock_luma_intra_mbaff;
1472 break;
1473 }
1474}
1475
1476static void set_aspect_ratio( x264_t *h, x264_param_t *param, int initial )
1477{
1478 /* VUI */
1479 if( param->vui.i_sar_width > 0 && param->vui.i_sar_height > 0 )
1480 {
1481 uint32_t i_w = param->vui.i_sar_width;
1482 uint32_t i_h = param->vui.i_sar_height;
1483 uint32_t old_w = h->param.vui.i_sar_width;
1484 uint32_t old_h = h->param.vui.i_sar_height;
1485
1486 x264_reduce_fraction( &i_w, &i_h );
1487
1488 while( i_w > 65535 || i_h > 65535 )
1489 {
1490 i_w /= 2;
1491 i_h /= 2;
1492 }
1493
1494 x264_reduce_fraction( &i_w, &i_h );
1495
1496 if( i_w != old_w || i_h != old_h || initial )
1497 {
1498 h->param.vui.i_sar_width = 0;
1499 h->param.vui.i_sar_height = 0;
1500 if( i_w == 0 || i_h == 0 )
1501 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "cannot create valid sample aspect ratio\n" );
1502 else
1503 {
1504 x264_log( h, initial?X264_LOG_INFO:X264_LOG_DEBUG, "using SAR=%d/%d\n", i_w, i_h );
1505 h->param.vui.i_sar_width = i_w;
1506 h->param.vui.i_sar_height = i_h;
1507 }
1508 }
1509 }
1510}
1511
1512/****************************************************************************
1513 * x264_encoder_open:
1514 ****************************************************************************/
1515x264_t *x264_encoder_open( x264_param_t *param, void *api )
1516{
1517 x264_t *h;
1518 char buf[1000], *p;
1519 int i_slicetype_length;
1520
1521 CHECKED_MALLOCZERO( h, sizeof(x264_t) );
1522
1523 /* Create a copy of param */
1524 memcpy( &h->param, param, sizeof(x264_param_t) );
1525 h->param.opaque = NULL;
1526 h->param.param_free = NULL;
1527
1528 if( h->param.psz_cqm_file )
1529 CHECKED_PARAM_STRDUP( h->param.psz_cqm_file, &h->param, h->param.psz_cqm_file );
1530 if( h->param.psz_dump_yuv )
1531 CHECKED_PARAM_STRDUP( h->param.psz_dump_yuv, &h->param, h->param.psz_dump_yuv );
1532 if( h->param.rc.psz_stat_out )
1533 CHECKED_PARAM_STRDUP( h->param.rc.psz_stat_out, &h->param, h->param.rc.psz_stat_out );
1534 if( h->param.rc.psz_stat_in )
1535 CHECKED_PARAM_STRDUP( h->param.rc.psz_stat_in, &h->param, h->param.rc.psz_stat_in );
1536 if( h->param.rc.psz_zones )
1537 CHECKED_PARAM_STRDUP( h->param.rc.psz_zones, &h->param, h->param.rc.psz_zones );
1538 if( h->param.psz_clbin_file )
1539 CHECKED_PARAM_STRDUP( h->param.psz_clbin_file, &h->param, h->param.psz_clbin_file );
1540
1541 if( param->param_free )
1542 {
1543 x264_param_cleanup( param );
1544 param->param_free( param );
1545 }
1546
1547 /* Save pointer to bit depth independent interface */
1548 h->api = api;
1549
1550#if HAVE_INTEL_DISPATCHER
1551 x264_intel_dispatcher_override();
1552#endif
1553
1554 if( x264_threading_init() )
1555 {
1556 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "unable to initialize threading\n" );
1557 goto fail;
1558 }
1559
1560 if( validate_parameters( h, 1 ) < 0 )
1561 goto fail;
1562
1563 if( h->param.psz_cqm_file )
1564 if( x264_cqm_parse_file( h, h->param.psz_cqm_file ) < 0 )
1565 goto fail;
1566
1567 x264_reduce_fraction( &h->param.i_fps_num, &h->param.i_fps_den );
1568 x264_reduce_fraction( &h->param.i_timebase_num, &h->param.i_timebase_den );
1569
1570 /* Init x264_t */
1571 h->i_frame = -1;
1572 h->i_frame_num = 0;
1573
1574 if( h->param.i_avcintra_class )
1575 h->i_idr_pic_id = h->param.i_avcintra_class > 200 ? 4 : 5;
1576 else
1577 h->i_idr_pic_id = 0;
1578
1579 if( (uint64_t)h->param.i_timebase_den * 2 > UINT32_MAX )
1580 {
1581 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "Effective timebase denominator %u exceeds H.264 maximum\n", h->param.i_timebase_den );
1582 goto fail;
1583 }
1584
1585 set_aspect_ratio( h, &h->param, 1 );
1586
1587 x264_sps_init( h->sps, h->param.i_sps_id, &h->param );
1588 x264_sps_init_scaling_list( h->sps, &h->param );
1589 x264_pps_init( h->pps, h->param.i_sps_id, &h->param, h->sps );
1590
1591 x264_validate_levels( h, 1 );
1592
1593 h->chroma_qp_table = i_chroma_qp_table + 12 + h->pps->i_chroma_qp_index_offset;
1594
1595 if( x264_cqm_init( h ) < 0 )
1596 goto fail;
1597
1598 h->mb.i_mb_width = h->sps->i_mb_width;
1599 h->mb.i_mb_height = h->sps->i_mb_height;
1600 h->mb.i_mb_count = h->mb.i_mb_width * h->mb.i_mb_height;
1601
1602 h->mb.chroma_h_shift = CHROMA_FORMAT == CHROMA_420 || CHROMA_FORMAT == CHROMA_422;
1603 h->mb.chroma_v_shift = CHROMA_FORMAT == CHROMA_420;
1604
1605 /* Adaptive MBAFF and subme 0 are not supported as we require halving motion
1606 * vectors during prediction, resulting in hpel mvs.
1607 * The chosen solution is to make MBAFF non-adaptive in this case. */
1608 h->mb.b_adaptive_mbaff = PARAM_INTERLACED && h->param.analyse.i_subpel_refine;
1609
1610 /* Init frames. */
1611 if( h->param.i_bframe_adaptive == X264_B_ADAPT_TRELLIS && !h->param.rc.b_stat_read )
1612 h->frames.i_delay = X264_MAX(h->param.i_bframe,3)*4;
1613 else
1614 h->frames.i_delay = h->param.i_bframe;
1615 if( h->param.rc.b_mb_tree || h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size )
1616 h->frames.i_delay = X264_MAX( h->frames.i_delay, h->param.rc.i_lookahead );
1617 i_slicetype_length = h->frames.i_delay;
1618 h->frames.i_delay += h->i_thread_frames - 1;
1619 h->frames.i_delay += h->param.i_sync_lookahead;
1620 h->frames.i_delay += h->param.b_vfr_input;
1621 h->frames.i_bframe_delay = h->param.i_bframe ? (h->param.i_bframe_pyramid ? 2 : 1) : 0;
1622
1623 h->frames.i_max_ref0 = h->param.i_frame_reference;
1624 h->frames.i_max_ref1 = X264_MIN( h->sps->vui.i_num_reorder_frames, h->param.i_frame_reference );
1625 h->frames.i_max_dpb = h->sps->vui.i_max_dec_frame_buffering;
1626 h->frames.b_have_lowres = !h->param.rc.b_stat_read
1627 && ( h->param.rc.i_rc_method == X264_RC_ABR
1628 || h->param.rc.i_rc_method == X264_RC_CRF
1629 || h->param.i_bframe_adaptive
1630 || h->param.i_scenecut_threshold
1631 || h->param.rc.b_mb_tree
1632 || h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred );
1633 h->frames.b_have_lowres |= h->param.rc.b_stat_read && h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size > 0;
1634 h->frames.b_have_sub8x8_esa = !!(h->param.analyse.inter & X264_ANALYSE_PSUB8x8);
1635
1636 h->frames.i_last_idr =
1637 h->frames.i_last_keyframe = - h->param.i_keyint_max;
1638 h->frames.i_input = 0;
1639 h->frames.i_largest_pts = h->frames.i_second_largest_pts = -1;
1640 h->frames.i_poc_last_open_gop = -1;
1641
1642 CHECKED_MALLOCZERO( h->cost_table, sizeof(*h->cost_table) );
1643 CHECKED_MALLOCZERO( h->frames.unused[0], (h->frames.i_delay + 3) * sizeof(x264_frame_t *) );
1644 /* Allocate room for max refs plus a few extra just in case. */
1645 CHECKED_MALLOCZERO( h->frames.unused[1], (h->i_thread_frames + X264_REF_MAX + 4) * sizeof(x264_frame_t *) );
1646 CHECKED_MALLOCZERO( h->frames.current, (h->param.i_sync_lookahead + h->param.i_bframe
1647 + h->i_thread_frames + 3) * sizeof(x264_frame_t *) );
1648 if( h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred > 0 )
1649 CHECKED_MALLOCZERO( h->frames.blank_unused, h->i_thread_frames * 4 * sizeof(x264_frame_t *) );
1650 h->i_ref[0] = h->i_ref[1] = 0;
1651 h->i_cpb_delay = h->i_coded_fields = h->i_disp_fields = 0;
1652 h->i_prev_duration = ((uint64_t)h->param.i_fps_den * h->sps->vui.i_time_scale) / ((uint64_t)h->param.i_fps_num * h->sps->vui.i_num_units_in_tick);
1653 h->i_disp_fields_last_frame = -1;
1654 x264_rdo_init();
1655
1656 /* init CPU functions */
1657#if (ARCH_X86 || ARCH_X86_64) && HIGH_BIT_DEPTH
1658 /* FIXME: Only 8-bit has been optimized for AVX-512 so far. The few AVX-512 functions
1659 * enabled in high bit-depth are insignificant and just causes potential issues with
1660 * unnecessary thermal throttling and whatnot, so keep it disabled for now. */
1661 h->param.cpu &= ~X264_CPU_AVX512;
1662#endif
1663 x264_predict_16x16_init( h->param.cpu, h->predict_16x16 );
1664 x264_predict_8x8c_init( h->param.cpu, h->predict_8x8c );
1665 x264_predict_8x16c_init( h->param.cpu, h->predict_8x16c );
1666 x264_predict_8x8_init( h->param.cpu, h->predict_8x8, &h->predict_8x8_filter );
1667 x264_predict_4x4_init( h->param.cpu, h->predict_4x4 );
1668 x264_pixel_init( h->param.cpu, &h->pixf );
1669 x264_dct_init( h->param.cpu, &h->dctf );
1670 x264_zigzag_init( h->param.cpu, &h->zigzagf_progressive, &h->zigzagf_interlaced );
1671 memcpy( &h->zigzagf, PARAM_INTERLACED ? &h->zigzagf_interlaced : &h->zigzagf_progressive, sizeof(h->zigzagf) );
1672 x264_mc_init( h->param.cpu, &h->mc, h->param.b_cpu_independent );
1673 x264_quant_init( h, h->param.cpu, &h->quantf );
1674 x264_deblock_init( h->param.cpu, &h->loopf, PARAM_INTERLACED );
1675 x264_bitstream_init( h->param.cpu, &h->bsf );
1676 if( h->param.b_cabac )
1677 x264_cabac_init( h );
1678 else
1679 x264_cavlc_init( h );
1680
1681 mbcmp_init( h );
1682 chroma_dsp_init( h );
1683
1684 p = buf + sprintf( buf, "using cpu capabilities:" );
1685 for( int i = 0; x264_cpu_names[i].flags; i++ )
1686 {
1687 if( !strcmp(x264_cpu_names[i].name, "SSE")
1688 && h->param.cpu & (X264_CPU_SSE2) )
1689 continue;
1690 if( !strcmp(x264_cpu_names[i].name, "SSE2")
1691 && h->param.cpu & (X264_CPU_SSE2_IS_FAST|X264_CPU_SSE2_IS_SLOW) )
1692 continue;
1693 if( !strcmp(x264_cpu_names[i].name, "SSE3")
1694 && (h->param.cpu & X264_CPU_SSSE3 || !(h->param.cpu & X264_CPU_CACHELINE_64)) )
1695 continue;
1696 if( !strcmp(x264_cpu_names[i].name, "SSE4.1")
1697 && (h->param.cpu & X264_CPU_SSE42) )
1698 continue;
1699 if( !strcmp(x264_cpu_names[i].name, "LZCNT")
1700 && (h->param.cpu & X264_CPU_BMI1) )
1701 continue;
1702 if( !strcmp(x264_cpu_names[i].name, "BMI1")
1703 && (h->param.cpu & X264_CPU_BMI2) )
1704 continue;
1705 if( !strcmp(x264_cpu_names[i].name, "FMA4")
1706 && (h->param.cpu & X264_CPU_FMA3) )
1707 continue;
1708 if( (h->param.cpu & x264_cpu_names[i].flags) == x264_cpu_names[i].flags
1709 && (!i || x264_cpu_names[i].flags != x264_cpu_names[i-1].flags) )
1710 p += sprintf( p, " %s", x264_cpu_names[i].name );
1711 }
1712 if( !h->param.cpu )
1713 p += sprintf( p, " none!" );
1714 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "%s\n", buf );
1715
1716 if( x264_analyse_init_costs( h ) )
1717 goto fail;
1718
1719 /* Must be volatile or else GCC will optimize it out. */
1720 volatile int temp = 392;
1721 if( x264_clz( temp ) != 23 )
1722 {
1723 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "CLZ test failed: x264 has been miscompiled!\n" );
1724#if ARCH_X86 || ARCH_X86_64
1725 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "Are you attempting to run an SSE4a/LZCNT-targeted build on a CPU that\n" );
1726 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "doesn't support it?\n" );
1727#endif
1728 goto fail;
1729 }
1730
1731 h->out.i_nal = 0;
1732 h->out.i_bitstream = x264_clip3f(
1733 h->param.i_width * h->param.i_height * 4
1734 * ( h->param.rc.i_rc_method == X264_RC_ABR
1735 ? pow( 0.95, h->param.rc.i_qp_min )
1736 : pow( 0.95, h->param.rc.i_qp_constant ) * X264_MAX( 1, h->param.rc.f_ip_factor ) ),
1737 1000000, INT_MAX/3
1738 );
1739
1740 h->nal_buffer_size = h->out.i_bitstream * 3/2 + 4 + 64; /* +4 for startcode, +64 for nal_escape assembly padding */
1741 CHECKED_MALLOC( h->nal_buffer, h->nal_buffer_size );
1742
1743 CHECKED_MALLOC( h->reconfig_h, sizeof(x264_t) );
1744
1745 if( h->param.i_threads > 1 &&
1746 x264_threadpool_init( &h->threadpool, h->param.i_threads, (void*)encoder_thread_init, h ) )
1747 goto fail;
1748 if( h->param.i_lookahead_threads > 1 &&
1749 x264_threadpool_init( &h->lookaheadpool, h->param.i_lookahead_threads, NULL, NULL ) )
1750 goto fail;
1751
1752#if HAVE_OPENCL
1753 if( h->param.b_opencl )
1754 {
1755 h->opencl.ocl = x264_opencl_load_library();
1756 if( !h->opencl.ocl )
1757 {
1758 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "failed to load OpenCL\n" );
1759 h->param.b_opencl = 0;
1760 }
1761 }
1762#endif
1763
1764 h->thread[0] = h;
1765 for( int i = 1; i < h->param.i_threads + !!h->param.i_sync_lookahead; i++ )
1766 CHECKED_MALLOC( h->thread[i], sizeof(x264_t) );
1767 if( h->param.i_lookahead_threads > 1 )
1768 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_lookahead_threads; i++ )
1769 {
1770 CHECKED_MALLOC( h->lookahead_thread[i], sizeof(x264_t) );
1771 *h->lookahead_thread[i] = *h;
1772 }
1773 *h->reconfig_h = *h;
1774
1775 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
1776 {
1777 int init_nal_count = h->param.i_slice_count + 3;
1778 int allocate_threadlocal_data = !h->param.b_sliced_threads || !i;
1779 if( i > 0 )
1780 *h->thread[i] = *h;
1781
1782 if( x264_pthread_mutex_init( &h->thread[i]->mutex, NULL ) )
1783 goto fail;
1784 if( x264_pthread_cond_init( &h->thread[i]->cv, NULL ) )
1785 goto fail;
1786
1787 if( allocate_threadlocal_data )
1788 {
1789 h->thread[i]->fdec = x264_frame_pop_unused( h, 1 );
1790 if( !h->thread[i]->fdec )
1791 goto fail;
1792 }
1793 else
1794 h->thread[i]->fdec = h->thread[0]->fdec;
1795
1796 CHECKED_MALLOC( h->thread[i]->out.p_bitstream, h->out.i_bitstream );
1797 /* Start each thread with room for init_nal_count NAL units; it'll realloc later if needed. */
1798 CHECKED_MALLOC( h->thread[i]->out.nal, init_nal_count*sizeof(x264_nal_t) );
1799 h->thread[i]->out.i_nals_allocated = init_nal_count;
1800
1801 if( allocate_threadlocal_data && x264_macroblock_cache_allocate( h->thread[i] ) < 0 )
1802 goto fail;
1803 }
1804
1805#if HAVE_OPENCL
1806 if( h->param.b_opencl && x264_opencl_lookahead_init( h ) < 0 )
1807 h->param.b_opencl = 0;
1808#endif
1809
1810 if( x264_lookahead_init( h, i_slicetype_length ) )
1811 goto fail;
1812
1813 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
1814 if( x264_macroblock_thread_allocate( h->thread[i], 0 ) < 0 )
1815 goto fail;
1816
1817 if( x264_ratecontrol_new( h ) < 0 )
1818 goto fail;
1819
1820 if( h->param.i_nal_hrd )
1821 {
1822 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_DEBUG, "HRD bitrate: %i bits/sec\n", h->sps->vui.hrd.i_bit_rate_unscaled );
1823 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_DEBUG, "CPB size: %i bits\n", h->sps->vui.hrd.i_cpb_size_unscaled );
1824 }
1825
1826 if( h->param.psz_dump_yuv )
1827 {
1828 /* create or truncate the reconstructed video file */
1829 FILE *f = x264_fopen( h->param.psz_dump_yuv, "w" );
1830 if( !f )
1831 {
1832 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "dump_yuv: can't write to %s\n", h->param.psz_dump_yuv );
1833 goto fail;
1834 }
1835 else if( !x264_is_regular_file( f ) )
1836 {
1837 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "dump_yuv: incompatible with non-regular file %s\n", h->param.psz_dump_yuv );
1838 fclose( f );
1839 goto fail;
1840 }
1841 fclose( f );
1842 }
1843
1844 const char *profile = h->sps->i_profile_idc == PROFILE_BASELINE ? "Constrained Baseline" :
1845 h->sps->i_profile_idc == PROFILE_MAIN ? "Main" :
1846 h->sps->i_profile_idc == PROFILE_HIGH ? "High" :
1847 h->sps->i_profile_idc == PROFILE_HIGH10 ?
1848 (h->sps->b_constraint_set3 ? "High 10 Intra" : "High 10") :
1849 h->sps->i_profile_idc == PROFILE_HIGH422 ?
1850 (h->sps->b_constraint_set3 ? "High 4:2:2 Intra" : "High 4:2:2") :
1851 h->sps->b_constraint_set3 ? "High 4:4:4 Intra" : "High 4:4:4 Predictive";
1852 char level[16];
1853 if( h->sps->i_level_idc == 9 || ( h->sps->i_level_idc == 11 && h->sps->b_constraint_set3 &&
1854 (h->sps->i_profile_idc == PROFILE_BASELINE || h->sps->i_profile_idc == PROFILE_MAIN) ) )
1855 strcpy( level, "1b" );
1856 else
1857 snprintf( level, sizeof(level), "%d.%d", h->sps->i_level_idc / 10, h->sps->i_level_idc % 10 );
1858
1859 static const char * const subsampling[4] = { "4:0:0", "4:2:0", "4:2:2", "4:4:4" };
1860 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "profile %s, level %s, %s, %d-bit\n",
1861 profile, level, subsampling[CHROMA_FORMAT], BIT_DEPTH );
1862
1863 return h;
1864fail:
1865 x264_free( h );
1866 return NULL;
1867}

1869/****************************************************************************/
1870static int encoder_try_reconfig( x264_t *h, x264_param_t *param, int *rc_reconfig )
1871{
1872 *rc_reconfig = 0;
1873 set_aspect_ratio( h, param, 0 );
1874#define COPY(var) h->param.var = param->var
1875 COPY( i_frame_reference ); // but never uses more refs than initially specified
1876 COPY( i_bframe_bias );
1877 if( h->param.i_scenecut_threshold )
1878 COPY( i_scenecut_threshold ); // can't turn it on or off, only vary the threshold
1879 COPY( b_deblocking_filter );
1880 COPY( i_deblocking_filter_alphac0 );
1881 COPY( i_deblocking_filter_beta );
1882 COPY( i_frame_packing );
1883 COPY( mastering_display );
1884 COPY( content_light_level );
1885 COPY( i_alternative_transfer );
1886 COPY( analyse.inter );
1887 COPY( analyse.intra );
1888 COPY( analyse.i_direct_mv_pred );
1889 /* Scratch buffer prevents me_range from being increased for esa/tesa */
1890 if( h->param.analyse.i_me_method < X264_ME_ESA || param->analyse.i_me_range < h->param.analyse.i_me_range )
1891 COPY( analyse.i_me_range );
1892 COPY( analyse.i_noise_reduction );
1893 /* We can't switch out of subme=0 during encoding. */
1894 if( h->param.analyse.i_subpel_refine )
1895 COPY( analyse.i_subpel_refine );
1896 COPY( analyse.i_trellis );
1897 COPY( analyse.b_chroma_me );
1898 COPY( analyse.b_dct_decimate );
1899 COPY( analyse.b_fast_pskip );
1900 COPY( analyse.b_mixed_references );
1901 COPY( analyse.f_psy_rd );
1902 COPY( analyse.f_psy_trellis );
1903 COPY( crop_rect );
1904 // can only twiddle these if they were enabled to begin with:
1905 if( h->param.analyse.i_me_method >= X264_ME_ESA || param->analyse.i_me_method < X264_ME_ESA )
1906 COPY( analyse.i_me_method );
1907 if( h->param.analyse.i_me_method >= X264_ME_ESA && !h->frames.b_have_sub8x8_esa )
1908 h->param.analyse.inter &= ~X264_ANALYSE_PSUB8x8;
1909 if( h->pps->b_transform_8x8_mode )
1910 COPY( analyse.b_transform_8x8 );
1911 if( h->frames.i_max_ref1 > 1 )
1912 COPY( i_bframe_pyramid );
1913 COPY( i_slice_max_size );
1914 COPY( i_slice_max_mbs );
1915 COPY( i_slice_min_mbs );
1916 COPY( i_slice_count );
1917 COPY( i_slice_count_max );
1918 COPY( b_tff );
1919
1920 /* VBV can't be turned on if it wasn't on to begin with */
1921 if( h->param.rc.i_vbv_max_bitrate > 0 && h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size > 0 &&
1922 param->rc.i_vbv_max_bitrate > 0 && param->rc.i_vbv_buffer_size > 0 )
1923 {
1924 *rc_reconfig |= h->param.rc.i_vbv_max_bitrate != param->rc.i_vbv_max_bitrate;
1925 *rc_reconfig |= h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size != param->rc.i_vbv_buffer_size;
1926 *rc_reconfig |= h->param.rc.i_bitrate != param->rc.i_bitrate;
1927 COPY( rc.i_vbv_max_bitrate );
1928 COPY( rc.i_vbv_buffer_size );
1929 COPY( rc.i_bitrate );
1930 }
1931 *rc_reconfig |= h->param.rc.f_rf_constant != param->rc.f_rf_constant;
1932 *rc_reconfig |= h->param.rc.f_rf_constant_max != param->rc.f_rf_constant_max;
1933 COPY( rc.f_rf_constant );
1934 COPY( rc.f_rf_constant_max );
1935#undef COPY
1936
1937 return validate_parameters( h, 0 );
1938}
1939
1940int x264_encoder_reconfig_apply( x264_t *h, x264_param_t *param )
1941{
1942 int rc_reconfig;
1943 int ret = encoder_try_reconfig( h, param, &rc_reconfig );
1944
1945 mbcmp_init( h );
1946 if( !ret )
1947 x264_sps_init_reconfigurable( h->sps, &h->param );
1948
1949 /* Supported reconfiguration options (1-pass only):
1950 * vbv-maxrate
1951 * vbv-bufsize
1952 * crf
1953 * bitrate (CBR only) */
1954 if( !ret && rc_reconfig )
1955 x264_ratecontrol_init_reconfigurable( h, 0 );
1956
1957 return ret;
1958}

1960/****************************************************************************
1961 * x264_encoder_reconfig:
1962 ****************************************************************************/
1963int x264_encoder_reconfig( x264_t *h, x264_param_t *param )
1964{
1965 h = h->thread[h->thread[0]->i_thread_phase];
1966 x264_param_t param_save = h->reconfig_h->param;
1967 h->reconfig_h->param = h->param;
1968
1969 int rc_reconfig;
1970 int ret = encoder_try_reconfig( h->reconfig_h, param, &rc_reconfig );
1971 if( !ret )
1972 h->reconfig = 1;
1973 else
1974 h->reconfig_h->param = param_save;
1975
1976 return ret;
1977}

1988/* internal usage */
1989static void nal_start( x264_t *h, int i_type, int i_ref_idc )
1990{
1991 x264_nal_t *nal = &h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal];
1992
1993 nal->i_ref_idc = i_ref_idc;
1994 nal->i_type = i_type;
1995 nal->b_long_startcode = 1;
1996
1997 nal->i_payload= 0;
1998 nal->p_payload= &h->out.p_bitstream[bs_pos( &h->out.bs ) / 8];
1999 nal->i_padding= 0;
2000}
2001
2002/* if number of allocated nals is not enough, re-allocate a larger one. */
2003static int nal_check_buffer( x264_t *h )
2004{
2005 if( h->out.i_nal >= h->out.i_nals_allocated )
2006 {
2007 x264_nal_t *new_out = x264_malloc( sizeof(x264_nal_t) * (h->out.i_nals_allocated*2) );
2008 if( !new_out )
2009 return -1;
2010 memcpy( new_out, h->out.nal, sizeof(x264_nal_t) * (h->out.i_nals_allocated) );
2011 x264_free( h->out.nal );
2012 h->out.nal = new_out;
2013 h->out.i_nals_allocated *= 2;
2014 }
2015 return 0;
2016}
2017
2018static int nal_end( x264_t *h )
2019{
2020 x264_nal_t *nal = &h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal];
2021 uint8_t *end = &h->out.p_bitstream[bs_pos( &h->out.bs ) / 8];
2022 nal->i_payload = end - nal->p_payload;
2023 /* Assembly implementation of nal_escape reads past the end of the input.
2024 * While undefined padding wouldn't actually affect the output, it makes valgrind unhappy. */
2025 memset( end, 0xff, 64 );
2026 if( h->param.nalu_process )
2027 h->param.nalu_process( (x264_t *)h->api, nal, h->fenc->opaque );
2028 h->out.i_nal++;
2029
2030 return nal_check_buffer( h );
2031}
2032
2033static int check_encapsulated_buffer( x264_t *h, x264_t *h0, int start,
2034 int64_t previous_nal_size, int64_t necessary_size )
2035{
2036 if( h0->nal_buffer_size < necessary_size )
2037 {
2038 necessary_size *= 2;
2039 if( necessary_size > INT_MAX )
2040 return -1;
2041 uint8_t *buf = x264_malloc( necessary_size );
2042 if( !buf )
2043 return -1;
2044 if( previous_nal_size )
2045 memcpy( buf, h0->nal_buffer, previous_nal_size );
2046
2047 intptr_t delta = buf - h0->nal_buffer;
2048 for( int i = 0; i < start; i++ )
2049 h->out.nal[i].p_payload += delta;
2050
2051 x264_free( h0->nal_buffer );
2052 h0->nal_buffer = buf;
2053 h0->nal_buffer_size = necessary_size;
2054 }
2055
2056 return 0;
2057}
2058
2059static int encoder_encapsulate_nals( x264_t *h, int start )
2060{
2061 x264_t *h0 = h->thread[0];
2062 int64_t nal_size = 0, previous_nal_size = 0;
2063
2064 if( h->param.nalu_process )
2065 {
2066 for( int i = start; i < h->out.i_nal; i++ )
2067 nal_size += h->out.nal[i].i_payload;
2068 if( nal_size > INT_MAX )
2069 return -1;
2070 return nal_size;
2071 }
2072
2073 for( int i = 0; i < start; i++ )
2074 previous_nal_size += h->out.nal[i].i_payload;
2075
2076 for( int i = start; i < h->out.i_nal; i++ )
2077 nal_size += h->out.nal[i].i_payload;
2078
2079 /* Worst-case NAL unit escaping: reallocate the buffer if it's too small. */
2080 int64_t necessary_size = previous_nal_size + nal_size * 3/2 + h->out.i_nal * 4 + 4 + 64;
2081 for( int i = start; i < h->out.i_nal; i++ )
2082 necessary_size += h->out.nal[i].i_padding;
2083 if( check_encapsulated_buffer( h, h0, start, previous_nal_size, necessary_size ) )
2084 return -1;
2085
2086 uint8_t *nal_buffer = h0->nal_buffer + previous_nal_size;
2087
2088 for( int i = start; i < h->out.i_nal; i++ )
2089 {
2090 h->out.nal[i].b_long_startcode = !i || h->out.nal[i].i_type == NAL_SPS || h->out.nal[i].i_type == NAL_PPS ||
2091 h->param.i_avcintra_class;
2092 x264_nal_encode( h, nal_buffer, &h->out.nal[i] );
2093 nal_buffer += h->out.nal[i].i_payload;
2094 }
2095
2096 x264_emms();
2097
2098 return nal_buffer - (h0->nal_buffer + previous_nal_size);
2099}

2101/****************************************************************************
2102 * x264_encoder_headers:
2103 ****************************************************************************/
2104int x264_encoder_headers( x264_t *h, x264_nal_t **pp_nal, int *pi_nal )
2105{
2106 int frame_size = 0;
2107 /* init bitstream context */
2108 h->out.i_nal = 0;
2109 bs_init( &h->out.bs, h->out.p_bitstream, h->out.i_bitstream );
2110
2111 /* Write SEI, SPS and PPS. */
2112
2113 /* generate sequence parameters */
2114 nal_start( h, NAL_SPS, NAL_PRIORITY_HIGHEST );
2115 x264_sps_write( &h->out.bs, h->sps );
2116 if( nal_end( h ) )
2117 return -1;
2118
2119 /* generate picture parameters */
2120 nal_start( h, NAL_PPS, NAL_PRIORITY_HIGHEST );
2121 x264_pps_write( &h->out.bs, h->sps, h->pps );
2122 if( nal_end( h ) )
2123 return -1;
2124
2125 /* identify ourselves */
2126 nal_start( h, NAL_SEI, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
2127 if( x264_sei_version_write( h, &h->out.bs ) )
2128 return -1;
2129 if( nal_end( h ) )
2130 return -1;
2131
2132 frame_size = encoder_encapsulate_nals( h, 0 );
2133 if( frame_size < 0 )
2134 return -1;
2135
2136 /* now set output*/
2137 *pi_nal = h->out.i_nal;
2138 *pp_nal = &h->out.nal[0];
2139 h->out.i_nal = 0;
2140
2141 return frame_size;
2142}

2144/* Check to see whether we have chosen a reference list ordering different
2145 * from the standard's default. */
2146static inline void reference_check_reorder( x264_t *h )
2147{
2148 /* The reorder check doesn't check for missing frames, so just
2149 * force a reorder if one of the reference list is corrupt. */
2150 for( int i = 0; h->frames.reference[i]; i++ )
2151 if( h->frames.reference[i]->b_corrupt )
2152 {
2153 h->b_ref_reorder[0] = 1;
2154 return;
2155 }
2156 for( int list = 0; list <= (h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B); list++ )
2157 for( int i = 0; i < h->i_ref[list] - 1; i++ )
2158 {
2159 int framenum_diff = h->fref[list][i+1]->i_frame_num - h->fref[list][i]->i_frame_num;
2160 int poc_diff = h->fref[list][i+1]->i_poc - h->fref[list][i]->i_poc;
2161 /* P and B-frames use different default orders. */
2162 if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_P ? framenum_diff > 0 : list == 1 ? poc_diff < 0 : poc_diff > 0 )
2163 {
2164 h->b_ref_reorder[list] = 1;
2165 return;
2166 }
2167 }
2168}
2169
2170/* return -1 on failure, else return the index of the new reference frame */
2171static int weighted_reference_duplicate( x264_t *h, int i_ref, const x264_weight_t *w )
2172{
2173 int i = h->i_ref[0];
2174 int j = 1;
2175 x264_frame_t *newframe;
2176 if( i <= 1 ) /* empty list, definitely can't duplicate frame */
2177 return -1;
2178
2179 //Duplication is only used in X264_WEIGHTP_SMART
2180 if( h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred != X264_WEIGHTP_SMART )
2181 return -1;
2182
2183 /* Duplication is a hack to compensate for crappy rounding in motion compensation.
2184 * With high bit depth, it's not worth doing, so turn it off except in the case of
2185 * unweighted dupes. */
2186 if( BIT_DEPTH > 8 && w != x264_weight_none )
2187 return -1;
2188
2189 newframe = x264_frame_pop_blank_unused( h );
2190 if( !newframe )
2191 return -1;
2192
2193 //FIXME: probably don't need to copy everything
2194 *newframe = *h->fref[0][i_ref];
2195 newframe->i_reference_count = 1;
2196 newframe->orig = h->fref[0][i_ref];
2197 newframe->b_duplicate = 1;
2198 memcpy( h->fenc->weight[j], w, sizeof(h->fenc->weight[i]) );
2199
2200 /* shift the frames to make space for the dupe. */
2201 h->b_ref_reorder[0] = 1;
2202 if( h->i_ref[0] < X264_REF_MAX )
2203 ++h->i_ref[0];
2204 h->fref[0][X264_REF_MAX-1] = NULL;
2205 x264_frame_unshift( &h->fref[0][j], newframe );
2206
2207 return j;
2208}
2209
2210static void weighted_pred_init( x264_t *h )
2211{
2212 /* for now no analysis and set all weights to nothing */
2213 for( int i_ref = 0; i_ref < h->i_ref[0]; i_ref++ )
2214 h->fenc->weighted[i_ref] = h->fref[0][i_ref]->filtered[0][0];
2215
2216 // FIXME: This only supports weighting of one reference frame
2217 // and duplicates of that frame.
2218 h->fenc->i_lines_weighted = 0;
2219
2220 for( int i_ref = 0; i_ref < (h->i_ref[0] << SLICE_MBAFF); i_ref++ )
2221 for( int i = 0; i < 3; i++ )
2222 h->sh.weight[i_ref][i].weightfn = NULL;
2223
2224
2225 if( h->sh.i_type != SLICE_TYPE_P || h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred <= 0 )
2226 return;
2227
2228 int i_padv = PADV << PARAM_INTERLACED;
2229 int denom = -1;
2230 int weightplane[2] = { 0, 0 };
2231 int buffer_next = 0;
2232 for( int i = 0; i < 3; i++ )
2233 {
2234 for( int j = 0; j < h->i_ref[0]; j++ )
2235 {
2236 if( h->fenc->weight[j][i].weightfn )
2237 {
2238 h->sh.weight[j][i] = h->fenc->weight[j][i];
2239 // if weight is useless, don't write it to stream
2240 if( h->sh.weight[j][i].i_scale == 1<<h->sh.weight[j][i].i_denom && h->sh.weight[j][i].i_offset == 0 )
2241 h->sh.weight[j][i].weightfn = NULL;
2242 else
2243 {
2244 if( !weightplane[!!i] )
2245 {
2246 weightplane[!!i] = 1;
2247 h->sh.weight[0][!!i].i_denom = denom = h->sh.weight[j][i].i_denom;
2248 assert( x264_clip3( denom, 0, 7 ) == denom );
2249 }
2250
2251 assert( h->sh.weight[j][i].i_denom == denom );
2252 if( !i )
2253 {
2254 h->fenc->weighted[j] = h->mb.p_weight_buf[buffer_next++] + h->fenc->i_stride[0] * i_padv + PADH_ALIGN;
2255 //scale full resolution frame
2256 if( h->param.i_threads == 1 )
2257 {
2258 pixel *src = h->fref[0][j]->filtered[0][0] - h->fref[0][j]->i_stride[0]*i_padv - PADH_ALIGN;
2259 pixel *dst = h->fenc->weighted[j] - h->fenc->i_stride[0]*i_padv - PADH_ALIGN;
2260 int stride = h->fenc->i_stride[0];
2261 int width = h->fenc->i_width[0] + PADH2;
2262 int height = h->fenc->i_lines[0] + i_padv*2;
2263 x264_weight_scale_plane( h, dst, stride, src, stride, width, height, &h->sh.weight[j][0] );
2264 h->fenc->i_lines_weighted = height;
2265 }
2266 }
2267 }
2268 }
2269 }
2270 }
2271
2272 if( weightplane[1] )
2273 for( int i = 0; i < h->i_ref[0]; i++ )
2274 {
2275 if( h->sh.weight[i][1].weightfn && !h->sh.weight[i][2].weightfn )
2276 {
2277 h->sh.weight[i][2].i_scale = 1 << h->sh.weight[0][1].i_denom;
2278 h->sh.weight[i][2].i_offset = 0;
2279 }
2280 else if( h->sh.weight[i][2].weightfn && !h->sh.weight[i][1].weightfn )
2281 {
2282 h->sh.weight[i][1].i_scale = 1 << h->sh.weight[0][1].i_denom;
2283 h->sh.weight[i][1].i_offset = 0;
2284 }
2285 }
2286
2287 if( !weightplane[0] )
2288 h->sh.weight[0][0].i_denom = 0;
2289 if( !weightplane[1] )
2290 h->sh.weight[0][1].i_denom = 0;
2291 h->sh.weight[0][2].i_denom = h->sh.weight[0][1].i_denom;
2292}
2293
2294static inline int reference_distance( x264_t *h, x264_frame_t *frame )
2295{
2296 if( h->param.i_frame_packing == 5 )
2297 return abs((h->fenc->i_frame&~1) - (frame->i_frame&~1)) +
2298 ((h->fenc->i_frame&1) != (frame->i_frame&1));
2299 else
2300 return abs(h->fenc->i_frame - frame->i_frame);
2301}
2302
2303static inline void reference_build_list( x264_t *h, int i_poc )
2304{
2305 int b_ok;
2306
2307 /* build ref list 0/1 */
2308 h->mb.pic.i_fref[0] = h->i_ref[0] = 0;
2309 h->mb.pic.i_fref[1] = h->i_ref[1] = 0;
2310 if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_I )
2311 return;
2312
2313 for( int i = 0; h->frames.reference[i]; i++ )
2314 {
2315 if( h->frames.reference[i]->b_corrupt )
2316 continue;
2317 if( h->frames.reference[i]->i_poc < i_poc )
2318 h->fref[0][h->i_ref[0]++] = h->frames.reference[i];
2319 else if( h->frames.reference[i]->i_poc > i_poc )
2320 h->fref[1][h->i_ref[1]++] = h->frames.reference[i];
2321 }
2322
2323 if( h->sh.i_mmco_remove_from_end )
2324 {
2325 /* Order ref0 for MMCO remove */
2326 do
2327 {
2328 b_ok = 1;
2329 for( int i = 0; i < h->i_ref[0] - 1; i++ )
2330 {
2331 if( h->fref[0][i]->i_frame < h->fref[0][i+1]->i_frame )
2332 {
2333 XCHG( x264_frame_t*, h->fref[0][i], h->fref[0][i+1] );
2334 b_ok = 0;
2335 break;
2336 }
2337 }
2338 } while( !b_ok );
2339
2340 for( int i = h->i_ref[0]-1; i >= h->i_ref[0] - h->sh.i_mmco_remove_from_end; i-- )
2341 {
2342 int diff = h->i_frame_num - h->fref[0][i]->i_frame_num;
2343 h->sh.mmco[h->sh.i_mmco_command_count].i_poc = h->fref[0][i]->i_poc;
2344 h->sh.mmco[h->sh.i_mmco_command_count++].i_difference_of_pic_nums = diff;
2345 }
2346 }
2347
2348 /* Order reference lists by distance from the current frame. */
2349 for( int list = 0; list < 2; list++ )
2350 {
2351 h->fref_nearest[list] = h->fref[list][0];
2352 do
2353 {
2354 b_ok = 1;
2355 for( int i = 0; i < h->i_ref[list] - 1; i++ )
2356 {
2357 if( list ? h->fref[list][i+1]->i_poc < h->fref_nearest[list]->i_poc
2358 : h->fref[list][i+1]->i_poc > h->fref_nearest[list]->i_poc )
2359 h->fref_nearest[list] = h->fref[list][i+1];
2360 if( reference_distance( h, h->fref[list][i] ) > reference_distance( h, h->fref[list][i+1] ) )
2361 {
2362 XCHG( x264_frame_t*, h->fref[list][i], h->fref[list][i+1] );
2363 b_ok = 0;
2364 break;
2365 }
2366 }
2367 } while( !b_ok );
2368 }
2369
2370 reference_check_reorder( h );
2371
2372 h->i_ref[1] = X264_MIN( h->i_ref[1], h->frames.i_max_ref1 );
2373 h->i_ref[0] = X264_MIN( h->i_ref[0], h->frames.i_max_ref0 );
2374 h->i_ref[0] = X264_MIN( h->i_ref[0], h->param.i_frame_reference ); // if reconfig() has lowered the limit
2375
2376 /* For Blu-ray compliance, don't reference frames outside of the minigop. */
2377 if( IS_X264_TYPE_B( h->fenc->i_type ) && h->param.b_bluray_compat )
2378 h->i_ref[0] = X264_MIN( h->i_ref[0], IS_X264_TYPE_B( h->fref[0][0]->i_type ) + 1 );
2379
2380 /* add duplicates */
2381 if( h->fenc->i_type == X264_TYPE_P )
2382 {
2383 int idx = -1;
2384 if( h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred >= X264_WEIGHTP_SIMPLE )
2385 {
2386 x264_weight_t w[3];
2387 w[1].weightfn = w[2].weightfn = NULL;
2388 if( h->param.rc.b_stat_read )
2389 x264_ratecontrol_set_weights( h, h->fenc );
2390
2391 if( !h->fenc->weight[0][0].weightfn )
2392 {
2393 h->fenc->weight[0][0].i_denom = 0;
2394 SET_WEIGHT( w[0], 1, 1, 0, -1 );
2395 idx = weighted_reference_duplicate( h, 0, w );
2396 }
2397 else
2398 {
2399 if( h->fenc->weight[0][0].i_scale == 1<<h->fenc->weight[0][0].i_denom )
2400 {
2401 SET_WEIGHT( h->fenc->weight[0][0], 1, 1, 0, h->fenc->weight[0][0].i_offset );
2402 }
2403 weighted_reference_duplicate( h, 0, x264_weight_none );
2404 if( h->fenc->weight[0][0].i_offset > -128 )
2405 {
2406 w[0] = h->fenc->weight[0][0];
2407 w[0].i_offset--;
2408 h->mc.weight_cache( h, &w[0] );
2409 idx = weighted_reference_duplicate( h, 0, w );
2410 }
2411 }
2412 }
2413 h->mb.ref_blind_dupe = idx;
2414 }
2415
2416 assert( h->i_ref[0] + h->i_ref[1] <= X264_REF_MAX );
2417 h->mb.pic.i_fref[0] = h->i_ref[0];
2418 h->mb.pic.i_fref[1] = h->i_ref[1];
2419}
2420
2421static void fdec_filter_row( x264_t *h, int mb_y, int pass )
2422{
2423 /* mb_y is the mb to be encoded next, not the mb to be filtered here */
2424 int b_hpel = h->fdec->b_kept_as_ref;
2425 int b_deblock = h->sh.i_disable_deblocking_filter_idc != 1;
2426 int b_end = mb_y == h->i_threadslice_end;
2427 int b_measure_quality = 1;
2428 int min_y = mb_y - (1 << SLICE_MBAFF);
2429 int b_start = min_y == h->i_threadslice_start;
2430 /* Even in interlaced mode, deblocking never modifies more than 4 pixels
2431 * above each MB, as bS=4 doesn't happen for the top of interlaced mbpairs. */
2432 int minpix_y = min_y*16 - 4 * !b_start;
2433 int maxpix_y = mb_y*16 - 4 * !b_end;
2434 b_deblock &= b_hpel || h->param.b_full_recon || h->param.psz_dump_yuv;
2435 if( h->param.b_sliced_threads )
2436 {
2437 switch( pass )
2438 {
2439 /* During encode: only do deblock if asked for */
2440 default:
2441 case 0:
2442 b_deblock &= h->param.b_full_recon;
2443 b_hpel = 0;
2444 break;
2445 /* During post-encode pass: do deblock if not done yet, do hpel for all
2446 * rows except those between slices. */
2447 case 1:
2448 b_deblock &= !h->param.b_full_recon;
2449 b_hpel &= !(b_start && min_y > 0);
2450 b_measure_quality = 0;
2451 break;
2452 /* Final pass: do the rows between slices in sequence. */
2453 case 2:
2454 b_deblock = 0;
2455 b_measure_quality = 0;
2456 break;
2457 }
2458 }
2459 if( mb_y & SLICE_MBAFF )
2460 return;
2461 if( min_y < h->i_threadslice_start )
2462 return;
2463
2464 if( b_deblock )
2465 for( int y = min_y; y < mb_y; y += (1 << SLICE_MBAFF) )
2466 x264_frame_deblock_row( h, y );
2467
2468 /* FIXME: Prediction requires different borders for interlaced/progressive mc,
2469 * but the actual image data is equivalent. For now, maintain this
2470 * consistency by copying deblocked pixels between planes. */
2471 if( PARAM_INTERLACED && (!h->param.b_sliced_threads || pass == 1) )
2472 for( int p = 0; p < h->fdec->i_plane; p++ )
2473 for( int i = minpix_y>>(CHROMA_V_SHIFT && p); i < maxpix_y>>(CHROMA_V_SHIFT && p); i++ )
2474 memcpy( h->fdec->plane_fld[p] + i*h->fdec->i_stride[p],
2475 h->fdec->plane[p] + i*h->fdec->i_stride[p],
2476 h->mb.i_mb_width*16*SIZEOF_PIXEL );
2477
2478 if( h->fdec->b_kept_as_ref && (!h->param.b_sliced_threads || pass == 1) )
2479 x264_frame_expand_border( h, h->fdec, min_y );
2480 if( b_hpel )
2481 {
2482 int end = mb_y == h->mb.i_mb_height;
2483 /* Can't do hpel until the previous slice is done encoding. */
2484 if( h->param.analyse.i_subpel_refine )
2485 {
2486 x264_frame_filter( h, h->fdec, min_y, end );
2487 x264_frame_expand_border_filtered( h, h->fdec, min_y, end );
2488 }
2489 }
2490
2491 if( SLICE_MBAFF && pass == 0 )
2492 for( int i = 0; i < 3; i++ )
2493 {
2494 XCHG( pixel *, h->intra_border_backup[0][i], h->intra_border_backup[3][i] );
2495 XCHG( pixel *, h->intra_border_backup[1][i], h->intra_border_backup[4][i] );
2496 }
2497
2498 if( h->i_thread_frames > 1 && h->fdec->b_kept_as_ref )
2499 x264_frame_cond_broadcast( h->fdec, mb_y*16 + (b_end ? 10000 : -(X264_THREAD_HEIGHT << SLICE_MBAFF)) );
2500
2501 if( b_measure_quality )
2502 {
2503 maxpix_y = X264_MIN( maxpix_y, h->param.i_height );
2504 if( h->param.analyse.b_psnr )
2505 {
2506 for( int p = 0; p < (CHROMA444 ? 3 : 1); p++ )
2507 h->stat.frame.i_ssd[p] += x264_pixel_ssd_wxh( &h->pixf,
2508 h->fdec->plane[p] + minpix_y * h->fdec->i_stride[p], h->fdec->i_stride[p],
2509 h->fenc->plane[p] + minpix_y * h->fenc->i_stride[p], h->fenc->i_stride[p],
2510 h->param.i_width, maxpix_y-minpix_y );
2511 if( !CHROMA444 )
2512 {
2513 uint64_t ssd_u, ssd_v;
2514 int v_shift = CHROMA_V_SHIFT;
2515 x264_pixel_ssd_nv12( &h->pixf,
2516 h->fdec->plane[1] + (minpix_y>>v_shift) * h->fdec->i_stride[1], h->fdec->i_stride[1],
2517 h->fenc->plane[1] + (minpix_y>>v_shift) * h->fenc->i_stride[1], h->fenc->i_stride[1],
2518 h->param.i_width>>1, (maxpix_y-minpix_y)>>v_shift, &ssd_u, &ssd_v );
2519 h->stat.frame.i_ssd[1] += ssd_u;
2520 h->stat.frame.i_ssd[2] += ssd_v;
2521 }
2522 }
2523
2524 if( h->param.analyse.b_ssim )
2525 {
2526 int ssim_cnt;
2527 x264_emms();
2528 /* offset by 2 pixels to avoid alignment of ssim blocks with dct blocks,
2529 * and overlap by 4 */
2530 minpix_y += b_start ? 2 : -6;
2531 h->stat.frame.f_ssim +=
2532 x264_pixel_ssim_wxh( &h->pixf,
2533 h->fdec->plane[0] + 2+minpix_y*h->fdec->i_stride[0], h->fdec->i_stride[0],
2534 h->fenc->plane[0] + 2+minpix_y*h->fenc->i_stride[0], h->fenc->i_stride[0],
2535 h->param.i_width-2, maxpix_y-minpix_y, h->scratch_buffer, &ssim_cnt );
2536 h->stat.frame.i_ssim_cnt += ssim_cnt;
2537 }
2538 }
2539}

2541static inline int reference_update( x264_t *h )
2542{
2543 if( !h->fdec->b_kept_as_ref )
2544 {
2545 if( h->i_thread_frames > 1 )
2546 {
2547 x264_frame_push_unused( h, h->fdec );
2548 h->fdec = x264_frame_pop_unused( h, 1 );
2549 if( !h->fdec )
2550 return -1;
2551 }
2552 return 0;
2553 }
2554
2555 /* apply mmco from previous frame. */
2556 for( int i = 0; i < h->sh.i_mmco_command_count; i++ )
2557 for( int j = 0; h->frames.reference[j]; j++ )
2558 if( h->frames.reference[j]->i_poc == h->sh.mmco[i].i_poc )
2559 x264_frame_push_unused( h, x264_frame_shift( &h->frames.reference[j] ) );
2560
2561 /* move frame in the buffer */
2562 x264_frame_push( h->frames.reference, h->fdec );
2563 if( h->frames.reference[h->sps->i_num_ref_frames] )
2564 x264_frame_push_unused( h, x264_frame_shift( h->frames.reference ) );
2565 h->fdec = x264_frame_pop_unused( h, 1 );
2566 if( !h->fdec )
2567 return -1;
2568 return 0;
2569}

2571static inline void reference_reset( x264_t *h )
2572{
2573 while( h->frames.reference[0] )
2574 x264_frame_push_unused( h, x264_frame_pop( h->frames.reference ) );
2575 h->fdec->i_poc =
2576 h->fenc->i_poc = 0;
2577}

2579static inline void reference_hierarchy_reset( x264_t *h )
2580{
2581 int ref;
2582 int b_hasdelayframe = 0;
2583
2584 /* look for delay frames -- chain must only contain frames that are disposable */
2585 for( int i = 0; h->frames.current[i] && IS_DISPOSABLE( h->frames.current[i]->i_type ); i++ )
2586 b_hasdelayframe |= h->frames.current[i]->i_coded
2587 != h->frames.current[i]->i_frame + h->sps->vui.i_num_reorder_frames;
2588
2589 /* This function must handle b-pyramid and clear frames for open-gop */
2590 if( h->param.i_bframe_pyramid != X264_B_PYRAMID_STRICT && !b_hasdelayframe && h->frames.i_poc_last_open_gop == -1 )
2591 return;
2592
2593 /* Remove last BREF. There will never be old BREFs in the
2594 * dpb during a BREF decode when pyramid == STRICT */
2595 for( ref = 0; h->frames.reference[ref]; ref++ )
2596 {
2597 if( ( h->param.i_bframe_pyramid == X264_B_PYRAMID_STRICT
2598 && h->frames.reference[ref]->i_type == X264_TYPE_BREF )
2599 || ( h->frames.reference[ref]->i_poc < h->frames.i_poc_last_open_gop
2600 && h->sh.i_type != SLICE_TYPE_B ) )
2601 {
2602 int diff = h->i_frame_num - h->frames.reference[ref]->i_frame_num;
2603 h->sh.mmco[h->sh.i_mmco_command_count].i_difference_of_pic_nums = diff;
2604 h->sh.mmco[h->sh.i_mmco_command_count++].i_poc = h->frames.reference[ref]->i_poc;
2605 x264_frame_push_unused( h, x264_frame_shift( &h->frames.reference[ref] ) );
2606 h->b_ref_reorder[0] = 1;
2607 ref--;
2608 }
2609 }
2610
2611 /* Prepare room in the dpb for the delayed display time of the later b-frame's */
2612 if( h->param.i_bframe_pyramid )
2613 h->sh.i_mmco_remove_from_end = X264_MAX( ref + 2 - h->frames.i_max_dpb, 0 );
2614}

2616static inline void slice_init( x264_t *h, int i_nal_type, int i_global_qp )
2617{
2618 /* ------------------------ Create slice header ----------------------- */
2619 if( i_nal_type == NAL_SLICE_IDR )
2620 {
2621 slice_header_init( h, &h->sh, h->sps, h->pps, h->i_idr_pic_id, h->i_frame_num, i_global_qp );
2622
2623 /* alternate id */
2624 if( h->param.i_avcintra_class )
2625 {
2626 switch( h->i_idr_pic_id )
2627 {
2628 case 5:
2629 h->i_idr_pic_id = 3;
2630 break;
2631 case 3:
2632 h->i_idr_pic_id = 4;
2633 break;
2634 case 4:
2635 default:
2636 h->i_idr_pic_id = 5;
2637 break;
2638 }
2639 }
2640 else
2641 h->i_idr_pic_id ^= 1;
2642 }
2643 else
2644 {
2645 slice_header_init( h, &h->sh, h->sps, h->pps, -1, h->i_frame_num, i_global_qp );
2646
2647 h->sh.i_num_ref_idx_l0_active = h->i_ref[0] <= 0 ? 1 : h->i_ref[0];
2648 h->sh.i_num_ref_idx_l1_active = h->i_ref[1] <= 0 ? 1 : h->i_ref[1];
2649 if( h->sh.i_num_ref_idx_l0_active != h->pps->i_num_ref_idx_l0_default_active ||
2650 (h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B && h->sh.i_num_ref_idx_l1_active != h->pps->i_num_ref_idx_l1_default_active) )
2651 {
2652 h->sh.b_num_ref_idx_override = 1;
2653 }
2654 }
2655
2656 if( h->fenc->i_type == X264_TYPE_BREF && h->param.b_bluray_compat && h->sh.i_mmco_command_count )
2657 {
2658 h->b_sh_backup = 1;
2659 h->sh_backup = h->sh;
2660 }
2661
2662 h->fdec->i_frame_num = h->sh.i_frame_num;
2663
2664 if( h->sps->i_poc_type == 0 )
2665 {
2666 h->sh.i_poc = h->fdec->i_poc;
2667 if( PARAM_INTERLACED )
2668 {
2669 h->sh.i_delta_poc_bottom = h->param.b_tff ? 1 : -1;
2670 h->sh.i_poc += h->sh.i_delta_poc_bottom == -1;
2671 }
2672 else
2673 h->sh.i_delta_poc_bottom = 0;
2674 h->fdec->i_delta_poc[0] = h->sh.i_delta_poc_bottom == -1;
2675 h->fdec->i_delta_poc[1] = h->sh.i_delta_poc_bottom == 1;
2676 }
2677 else
2678 {
2679 /* Nothing to do ? */
2680 }
2681
2682 x264_macroblock_slice_init( h );
2683}
