2697static ALWAYS_INLINE void bitstream_backup( x264_t *h, x264_bs_bak_t *bak, int i_skip, int full )
2698{
2699 if( full )
2700 {
2701 bak->stat = h->stat.frame;
2702 bak->last_qp = h->mb.i_last_qp;
2703 bak->last_dqp = h->mb.i_last_dqp;
2704 bak->field_decoding_flag = h->mb.field_decoding_flag;
2705 }
2706 else
2707 {
2708 bak->stat.i_mv_bits = h->stat.frame.i_mv_bits;
2709 bak->stat.i_tex_bits = h->stat.frame.i_tex_bits;
2710 }
2711 /* In the per-MB backup, we don't need the contexts because flushing the CABAC
2712 * encoder has no context dependency and in this case, a slice is ended (and
2713 * thus the content of all contexts are thrown away). */
2714 if( h->param.b_cabac )
2715 {
2716 if( full )
2717 memcpy( &bak->cabac, &h->cabac, sizeof(x264_cabac_t) );
2718 else
2719 memcpy( &bak->cabac, &h->cabac, offsetof(x264_cabac_t, f8_bits_encoded) );
2720 /* x264's CABAC writer modifies the previous byte during carry, so it has to be
2721 * backed up. */
2722 bak->cabac_prevbyte = h->cabac.p[-1];
2723 }
2724 else
2725 {
2726 bak->bs = h->out.bs;
2727 bak->skip = i_skip;
2728 }
2729}
2730
2731static ALWAYS_INLINE void bitstream_restore( x264_t *h, x264_bs_bak_t *bak, int *skip, int full )
2732{
2733 if( full )
2734 {
2735 h->stat.frame = bak->stat;
2736 h->mb.i_last_qp = bak->last_qp;
2737 h->mb.i_last_dqp = bak->last_dqp;
2738 h->mb.field_decoding_flag = bak->field_decoding_flag;
2739 }
2740 else
2741 {
2742 h->stat.frame.i_mv_bits = bak->stat.i_mv_bits;
2743 h->stat.frame.i_tex_bits = bak->stat.i_tex_bits;
2744 }
2745 if( h->param.b_cabac )
2746 {
2747 if( full )
2748 memcpy( &h->cabac, &bak->cabac, sizeof(x264_cabac_t) );
2749 else
2750 memcpy( &h->cabac, &bak->cabac, offsetof(x264_cabac_t, f8_bits_encoded) );
2751 h->cabac.p[-1] = bak->cabac_prevbyte;
2752 }
2753 else
2754 {
2755 h->out.bs = bak->bs;
2756 *skip = bak->skip;
2757 }
2758}
2759
2760static intptr_t slice_write( x264_t *h )
2761{
2762 int i_skip;
2763 int mb_xy, i_mb_x, i_mb_y;
2764 /* NALUs other than the first use a 3-byte startcode.
2765 * Add one extra byte for the rbsp, and one more for the final CABAC putbyte.
2766 * Then add an extra 5 bytes just in case, to account for random NAL escapes and
2767 * other inaccuracies. */
2768 int overhead_guess = (NALU_OVERHEAD - (h->param.b_annexb && h->out.i_nal)) + 1 + h->param.b_cabac + 5;
2769 int slice_max_size = h->param.i_slice_max_size > 0 ? (h->param.i_slice_max_size-overhead_guess)*8 : 0;
2770 int back_up_bitstream_cavlc = !h->param.b_cabac && h->sps->i_profile_idc < PROFILE_HIGH;
2771 int back_up_bitstream = slice_max_size || back_up_bitstream_cavlc;
2772 int starting_bits = bs_pos(&h->out.bs);
2773 int b_deblock = h->sh.i_disable_deblocking_filter_idc != 1;
2774 int b_hpel = h->fdec->b_kept_as_ref;
2775 int orig_last_mb = h->sh.i_last_mb;
2776 int thread_last_mb = h->i_threadslice_end * h->mb.i_mb_width - 1;
2777 uint8_t *last_emu_check;
2778#define BS_BAK_SLICE_MAX_SIZE 0
2779#define BS_BAK_CAVLC_OVERFLOW 1
2780#define BS_BAK_SLICE_MIN_MBS 2
2781#define BS_BAK_ROW_VBV 3
2782 x264_bs_bak_t bs_bak[4];
2783 b_deblock &= b_hpel || h->param.b_full_recon || h->param.psz_dump_yuv;
2784 bs_realign( &h->out.bs );
2785
2786 /* Slice */
2787 nal_start( h, h->i_nal_type, h->i_nal_ref_idc );
2788 h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal].i_first_mb = h->sh.i_first_mb;
2789
2790 /* Slice header */
2791 x264_macroblock_thread_init( h );
2792
2793 /* Set the QP equal to the first QP in the slice for more accurate CABAC initialization. */
2794 h->mb.i_mb_xy = h->sh.i_first_mb;
2795 h->sh.i_qp = x264_ratecontrol_mb_qp( h );
2796 h->sh.i_qp = SPEC_QP( h->sh.i_qp );
2797 h->sh.i_qp_delta = h->sh.i_qp - h->pps->i_pic_init_qp;
2798
2799 slice_header_write( &h->out.bs, &h->sh, h->i_nal_ref_idc );
2800 if( h->param.b_cabac )
2801 {
2802 /* alignment needed */
2803 bs_align_1( &h->out.bs );
2804
2805 /* init cabac */
2806 x264_cabac_context_init( h, &h->cabac, h->sh.i_type, x264_clip3( h->sh.i_qp-QP_BD_OFFSET, 0, 51 ), h->sh.i_cabac_init_idc );
2807 x264_cabac_encode_init ( &h->cabac, h->out.bs.p, h->out.bs.p_end );
2808 last_emu_check = h->cabac.p;
2809 }
2810 else
2811 last_emu_check = h->out.bs.p;
2812 h->mb.i_last_qp = h->sh.i_qp;
2813 h->mb.i_last_dqp = 0;
2814 h->mb.field_decoding_flag = 0;
2815
2816 i_mb_y = h->sh.i_first_mb / h->mb.i_mb_width;
2817 i_mb_x = h->sh.i_first_mb % h->mb.i_mb_width;
2818 i_skip = 0;
2819
2820 while( 1 )
2821 {
2822 mb_xy = i_mb_x + i_mb_y * h->mb.i_mb_width;
2823 int mb_spos = bs_pos(&h->out.bs) + x264_cabac_pos(&h->cabac);
2824
2825 if( i_mb_x == 0 )
2826 {
2827 if( bitstream_check_buffer( h ) )
2828 return -1;
2829 if( !(i_mb_y & SLICE_MBAFF) && h->param.rc.i_vbv_buffer_size )
2830 bitstream_backup( h, &bs_bak[BS_BAK_ROW_VBV], i_skip, 1 );
2831 if( !h->mb.b_reencode_mb )
2832 fdec_filter_row( h, i_mb_y, 0 );
2833 }
2834
2835 if( back_up_bitstream )
2836 {
2837 if( back_up_bitstream_cavlc )
2838 bitstream_backup( h, &bs_bak[BS_BAK_CAVLC_OVERFLOW], i_skip, 0 );
2839 if( slice_max_size && !(i_mb_y & SLICE_MBAFF) )
2840 {
2841 bitstream_backup( h, &bs_bak[BS_BAK_SLICE_MAX_SIZE], i_skip, 0 );
2842 if( (thread_last_mb+1-mb_xy) == h->param.i_slice_min_mbs )
2843 bitstream_backup( h, &bs_bak[BS_BAK_SLICE_MIN_MBS], i_skip, 0 );
2844 }
2845 }
2846
2847 if( PARAM_INTERLACED )
2848 {
2849 if( h->mb.b_adaptive_mbaff )
2850 {
2851 if( !(i_mb_y&1) )
2852 {
2853 /* FIXME: VSAD is fast but fairly poor at choosing the best interlace type. */
2854 h->mb.b_interlaced = x264_field_vsad( h, i_mb_x, i_mb_y );
2855 memcpy( &h->zigzagf, MB_INTERLACED ? &h->zigzagf_interlaced : &h->zigzagf_progressive, sizeof(h->zigzagf) );
2856 if( !MB_INTERLACED && (i_mb_y+2) == h->mb.i_mb_height )
2857 x264_expand_border_mbpair( h, i_mb_x, i_mb_y );
2858 }
2859 }
2860 h->mb.field[mb_xy] = MB_INTERLACED;
2861 }
2862
2863 /* load cache */
2864 if( SLICE_MBAFF )
2865 x264_macroblock_cache_load_interlaced( h, i_mb_x, i_mb_y );
2866 else
2867 x264_macroblock_cache_load_progressive( h, i_mb_x, i_mb_y );
2868
2869 x264_macroblock_analyse( h );
2870
2871 /* encode this macroblock -> be careful it can change the mb type to P_SKIP if needed */
2872reencode:
2873 x264_macroblock_encode( h );
2874
2875 if( h->param.b_cabac )
2876 {
2877 if( mb_xy > h->sh.i_first_mb && !(SLICE_MBAFF && (i_mb_y&1)) )
2878 x264_cabac_encode_terminal( &h->cabac );
2879
2880 if( IS_SKIP( h->mb.i_type ) )
2881 x264_cabac_mb_skip( h, 1 );
2882 else
2883 {
2884 if( h->sh.i_type != SLICE_TYPE_I )
2885 x264_cabac_mb_skip( h, 0 );
2886 x264_macroblock_write_cabac( h, &h->cabac );
2887 }
2888 }
2889 else
2890 {
2891 if( IS_SKIP( h->mb.i_type ) )
2892 i_skip++;
2893 else
2894 {
2895 if( h->sh.i_type != SLICE_TYPE_I )
2896 {
2897 bs_write_ue( &h->out.bs, i_skip ); /* skip run */
2898 i_skip = 0;
2899 }
2900 x264_macroblock_write_cavlc( h );
2901 /* If there was a CAVLC level code overflow, try again at a higher QP. */
2902 if( h->mb.b_overflow )
2903 {
2904 h->mb.i_chroma_qp = h->chroma_qp_table[++h->mb.i_qp];
2905 h->mb.i_skip_intra = 0;
2906 h->mb.b_skip_mc = 0;
2907 h->mb.b_overflow = 0;
2908 bitstream_restore( h, &bs_bak[BS_BAK_CAVLC_OVERFLOW], &i_skip, 0 );
2909 goto reencode;
2910 }
2911 }
2912 }
2913
2914 int total_bits = bs_pos(&h->out.bs) + x264_cabac_pos(&h->cabac);
2915 int mb_size = total_bits - mb_spos;
2916
2917 if( slice_max_size && (!SLICE_MBAFF || (i_mb_y&1)) )
2918 {
2919 /* Count the skip run, just in case. */
2920 if( !h->param.b_cabac )
2921 total_bits += bs_size_ue_big( i_skip );
2922 /* Check for escape bytes. */
2923 uint8_t *end = h->param.b_cabac ? h->cabac.p : h->out.bs.p;
2924 for( ; last_emu_check < end - 2; last_emu_check++ )
2925 if( last_emu_check[0] == 0 && last_emu_check[1] == 0 && last_emu_check[2] <= 3 )
2926 {
2927 slice_max_size -= 8;
2928 last_emu_check++;
2929 }
2930 /* We'll just re-encode this last macroblock if we go over the max slice size. */
2931 if( total_bits - starting_bits > slice_max_size && !h->mb.b_reencode_mb )
2932 {
2933 if( !x264_frame_new_slice( h, h->fdec ) )
2934 {
2935 /* Handle the most obnoxious slice-min-mbs edge case: we need to end the slice
2936 * because it's gone over the maximum size, but doing so would violate slice-min-mbs.
2937 * If possible, roll back to the last checkpoint and try again.
2938 * We could try raising QP, but that would break in the case where a slice spans multiple
2939 * rows, which the re-encoding infrastructure can't currently handle. */
2940 if( mb_xy <= thread_last_mb && (thread_last_mb+1-mb_xy) < h->param.i_slice_min_mbs )
2941 {
2942 if( thread_last_mb-h->param.i_slice_min_mbs < h->sh.i_first_mb+h->param.i_slice_min_mbs )
2943 {
2944 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "slice-max-size violated (frame %d, cause: slice-min-mbs)\n", h->i_frame );
2945 slice_max_size = 0;
2946 goto cont;
2947 }
2948 bitstream_restore( h, &bs_bak[BS_BAK_SLICE_MIN_MBS], &i_skip, 0 );
2949 h->mb.b_reencode_mb = 1;
2950 h->sh.i_last_mb = thread_last_mb-h->param.i_slice_min_mbs;
2951 break;
2952 }
2953 if( mb_xy-SLICE_MBAFF*h->mb.i_mb_stride != h->sh.i_first_mb )
2954 {
2955 bitstream_restore( h, &bs_bak[BS_BAK_SLICE_MAX_SIZE], &i_skip, 0 );
2956 h->mb.b_reencode_mb = 1;
2957 if( SLICE_MBAFF )
2958 {
2959 // set to bottom of previous mbpair
2960 if( i_mb_x )
2961 h->sh.i_last_mb = mb_xy-1+h->mb.i_mb_stride*(!(i_mb_y&1));
2962 else
2963 h->sh.i_last_mb = (i_mb_y-2+!(i_mb_y&1))*h->mb.i_mb_stride + h->mb.i_mb_width - 1;
2964 }
2965 else
2966 h->sh.i_last_mb = mb_xy-1;
2967 break;
2968 }
2969 else
2970 h->sh.i_last_mb = mb_xy;
2971 }
2972 else
2973 slice_max_size = 0;
2974 }
2975 }
2976cont:
2977 h->mb.b_reencode_mb = 0;
2978
2979 /* save cache */
2980 x264_macroblock_cache_save( h );
2981
2982 if( x264_ratecontrol_mb( h, mb_size ) < 0 )
2983 {
2984 bitstream_restore( h, &bs_bak[BS_BAK_ROW_VBV], &i_skip, 1 );
2985 h->mb.b_reencode_mb = 1;
2986 i_mb_x = 0;
2987 i_mb_y = i_mb_y - SLICE_MBAFF;
2988 h->mb.i_mb_prev_xy = i_mb_y * h->mb.i_mb_stride - 1;
2989 h->sh.i_last_mb = orig_last_mb;
2990 continue;
2991 }
2992
2993 /* accumulate mb stats */
2994 h->stat.frame.i_mb_count[h->mb.i_type]++;
2995
2996 int b_intra = IS_INTRA( h->mb.i_type );
2997 int b_skip = IS_SKIP( h->mb.i_type );
2998 if( h->param.i_log_level >= X264_LOG_INFO || h->param.rc.b_stat_write )
2999 {
3000 if( !b_intra && !b_skip && !IS_DIRECT( h->mb.i_type ) )
3001 {
3002 if( h->mb.i_partition != D_8x8 )
3003 h->stat.frame.i_mb_partition[h->mb.i_partition] += 4;
3004 else
3005 for( int i = 0; i < 4; i++ )
3006 h->stat.frame.i_mb_partition[h->mb.i_sub_partition[i]] ++;
3007 if( h->param.i_frame_reference > 1 )
3008 for( int i_list = 0; i_list <= (h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B); i_list++ )
3009 for( int i = 0; i < 4; i++ )
3010 {
3011 int i_ref = h->mb.cache.ref[i_list][ x264_scan8[4*i] ];
3012 if( i_ref >= 0 )
3013 h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_ref[i_list][i_ref] ++;
3014 }
3015 }
3016 }
3017
3018 if( h->param.i_log_level >= X264_LOG_INFO )
3019 {
3020 if( h->mb.i_cbp_luma | h->mb.i_cbp_chroma )
3021 {
3022 if( CHROMA444 )
3023 {
3024 for( int i = 0; i < 4; i++ )
3025 if( h->mb.i_cbp_luma & (1 << i) )
3026 for( int p = 0; p < 3; p++ )
3027 {
3028 int s8 = i*4+p*16;
3029 int nnz8x8 = M16( &h->mb.cache.non_zero_count[x264_scan8[s8]+0] )
3030 | M16( &h->mb.cache.non_zero_count[x264_scan8[s8]+8] );
3031 h->stat.frame.i_mb_cbp[!b_intra + p*2] += !!nnz8x8;
3032 }
3033 }
3034 else
3035 {
3036 int cbpsum = (h->mb.i_cbp_luma&1) + ((h->mb.i_cbp_luma>>1)&1)
3037 + ((h->mb.i_cbp_luma>>2)&1) + (h->mb.i_cbp_luma>>3);
3038 h->stat.frame.i_mb_cbp[!b_intra + 0] += cbpsum;
3039 h->stat.frame.i_mb_cbp[!b_intra + 2] += !!h->mb.i_cbp_chroma;
3040 h->stat.frame.i_mb_cbp[!b_intra + 4] += h->mb.i_cbp_chroma >> 1;
3041 }
3042 }
3043 if( h->mb.i_cbp_luma && !b_intra )
3044 {
3045 h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_8x8dct[0] ++;
3046 h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_8x8dct[1] += h->mb.b_transform_8x8;
3047 }
3048 if( b_intra && h->mb.i_type != I_PCM )
3049 {
3050 if( h->mb.i_type == I_16x16 )
3051 h->stat.frame.i_mb_pred_mode[0][h->mb.i_intra16x16_pred_mode]++;
3052 else if( h->mb.i_type == I_8x8 )
3053 for( int i = 0; i < 16; i += 4 )
3054 h->stat.frame.i_mb_pred_mode[1][h->mb.cache.intra4x4_pred_mode[x264_scan8[i]]]++;
3055 else //if( h->mb.i_type == I_4x4 )
3056 for( int i = 0; i < 16; i++ )
3057 h->stat.frame.i_mb_pred_mode[2][h->mb.cache.intra4x4_pred_mode[x264_scan8[i]]]++;
3058 h->stat.frame.i_mb_pred_mode[3][x264_mb_chroma_pred_mode_fix[h->mb.i_chroma_pred_mode]]++;
3059 }
3060 h->stat.frame.i_mb_field[b_intra?0:b_skip?2:1] += MB_INTERLACED;
3061 }
3062
3063 /* calculate deblock strength values (actual deblocking is done per-row along with hpel) */
3064 if( b_deblock )
3065 x264_macroblock_deblock_strength( h );
3066
3067 if( mb_xy == h->sh.i_last_mb )
3068 break;
3069
3070 if( SLICE_MBAFF )
3071 {
3072 i_mb_x += i_mb_y & 1;
3073 i_mb_y ^= i_mb_x < h->mb.i_mb_width;
3074 }
3075 else
3076 i_mb_x++;
3077 if( i_mb_x == h->mb.i_mb_width )
3078 {
3079 i_mb_y++;
3080 i_mb_x = 0;
3081 }
3082 }
3083 if( h->sh.i_last_mb < h->sh.i_first_mb )
3084 return 0;
3085
3086 h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal].i_last_mb = h->sh.i_last_mb;
3087
3088 if( h->param.b_cabac )
3089 {
3090 x264_cabac_encode_flush( h, &h->cabac );
3091 h->out.bs.p = h->cabac.p;
3092 }
3093 else
3094 {
3095 if( i_skip > 0 )
3096 bs_write_ue( &h->out.bs, i_skip ); /* last skip run */
3097 /* rbsp_slice_trailing_bits */
3098 bs_rbsp_trailing( &h->out.bs );
3099 bs_flush( &h->out.bs );
3100 }
3101 if( nal_end( h ) )
3102 return -1;
3103
3104 if( h->sh.i_last_mb == (h->i_threadslice_end * h->mb.i_mb_width - 1) )
3105 {
3106 h->stat.frame.i_misc_bits = bs_pos( &h->out.bs )
3107 + (h->out.i_nal*NALU_OVERHEAD * 8)
3108 - h->stat.frame.i_tex_bits
3109 - h->stat.frame.i_mv_bits;
3110 fdec_filter_row( h, h->i_threadslice_end, 0 );
3111
3112 if( h->param.b_sliced_threads )
3113 {
3114 /* Tell the main thread we're done. */
3115 x264_threadslice_cond_broadcast( h, 1 );
3116 /* Do hpel now */
3117 for( int mb_y = h->i_threadslice_start; mb_y <= h->i_threadslice_end; mb_y++ )
3118 fdec_filter_row( h, mb_y, 1 );
3119 x264_threadslice_cond_broadcast( h, 2 );
3120 /* Do the first row of hpel, now that the previous slice is done */
3121 if( h->i_thread_idx > 0 )
3122 {
3123 x264_threadslice_cond_wait( h->thread[h->i_thread_idx-1], 2 );
3124 fdec_filter_row( h, h->i_threadslice_start + (1 << SLICE_MBAFF), 2 );
3125 }
3126 }
3127
3128 /* Free mb info after the last thread's done using it */
3129 if( h->fdec->mb_info_free && (!h->param.b_sliced_threads || h->i_thread_idx == (h->param.i_threads-1)) )
3130 {
3131 h->fdec->mb_info_free( h->fdec->mb_info );
3132 h->fdec->mb_info = NULL;
3133 h->fdec->mb_info_free = NULL;
3134 }
3135 }
3136
3137 return 0;
3138}

3140static void thread_sync_context( x264_t *dst, x264_t *src )
3141{
3142 if( dst == src )
3143 return;
3144
3145 // reference counting
3146 for( x264_frame_t **f = src->frames.reference; *f; f++ )
3147 (*f)->i_reference_count++;
3148 for( x264_frame_t **f = dst->frames.reference; *f; f++ )
3149 x264_frame_push_unused( src, *f );
3150 src->fdec->i_reference_count++;
3151 x264_frame_push_unused( src, dst->fdec );
3152
3153 // copy everything except the per-thread pointers and the constants.
3154 memcpy( &dst->i_frame, &src->i_frame, offsetof(x264_t, mb.base) - offsetof(x264_t, i_frame) );
3155 dst->param = src->param;
3156 dst->stat = src->stat;
3157 dst->pixf = src->pixf;
3158 dst->reconfig = src->reconfig;
3159}
3160
3161static void thread_sync_stat( x264_t *dst, x264_t *src )
3162{
3163 if( dst != src )
3164 memcpy( &dst->stat, &src->stat, offsetof(x264_t, stat.frame) - offsetof(x264_t, stat) );
3165}
3166
3167static void *slices_write( x264_t *h )
3168{
3169 int i_slice_num = 0;
3170 int last_thread_mb = h->sh.i_last_mb;
3171 int round_bias = h->param.i_avcintra_class ? 0 : h->param.i_slice_count/2;
3172
3173 /* init stats */
3174 memset( &h->stat.frame, 0, sizeof(h->stat.frame) );
3175 h->mb.b_reencode_mb = 0;
3176 while( h->sh.i_first_mb + SLICE_MBAFF*h->mb.i_mb_stride <= last_thread_mb )
3177 {
3178 h->sh.i_last_mb = last_thread_mb;
3179 if( !i_slice_num || !x264_frame_new_slice( h, h->fdec ) )
3180 {
3181 if( h->param.i_slice_max_mbs )
3182 {
3183 if( SLICE_MBAFF )
3184 {
3185 // convert first to mbaff form, add slice-max-mbs, then convert back to normal form
3186 int last_mbaff = 2*(h->sh.i_first_mb % h->mb.i_mb_width)
3187 + h->mb.i_mb_width*(h->sh.i_first_mb / h->mb.i_mb_width)
3188 + h->param.i_slice_max_mbs - 1;
3189 int last_x = (last_mbaff % (2*h->mb.i_mb_width))/2;
3190 int last_y = (last_mbaff / (2*h->mb.i_mb_width))*2 + 1;
3191 h->sh.i_last_mb = last_x + h->mb.i_mb_stride*last_y;
3192 }
3193 else
3194 {
3195 h->sh.i_last_mb = h->sh.i_first_mb + h->param.i_slice_max_mbs - 1;
3196 if( h->sh.i_last_mb < last_thread_mb && last_thread_mb - h->sh.i_last_mb < h->param.i_slice_min_mbs )
3197 h->sh.i_last_mb = last_thread_mb - h->param.i_slice_min_mbs;
3198 }
3199 i_slice_num++;
3200 }
3201 else if( h->param.i_slice_count && !h->param.b_sliced_threads )
3202 {
3203 int height = h->mb.i_mb_height >> PARAM_INTERLACED;
3204 int width = h->mb.i_mb_width << PARAM_INTERLACED;
3205 i_slice_num++;
3206 h->sh.i_last_mb = (height * i_slice_num + round_bias) / h->param.i_slice_count * width - 1;
3207 }
3208 }
3209 h->sh.i_last_mb = X264_MIN( h->sh.i_last_mb, last_thread_mb );
3210 if( slice_write( h ) )
3211 goto fail;
3212 h->sh.i_first_mb = h->sh.i_last_mb + 1;
3213 // if i_first_mb is not the last mb in a row then go to the next mb in MBAFF order
3214 if( SLICE_MBAFF && h->sh.i_first_mb % h->mb.i_mb_width )
3215 h->sh.i_first_mb -= h->mb.i_mb_stride;
3216 }
3217
3218 return (void *)0;
3219
3220fail:
3221 /* Tell other threads we're done, so they wouldn't wait for it */
3222 if( h->param.b_sliced_threads )
3223 x264_threadslice_cond_broadcast( h, 2 );
3224 return (void *)-1;
3225}
3226
3227static int threaded_slices_write( x264_t *h )
3228{
3229 int round_bias = h->param.i_avcintra_class ? 0 : h->param.i_slice_count/2;
3230
3231 /* set first/last mb and sync contexts */
3232 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
3233 {
3234 x264_t *t = h->thread[i];
3235 if( i )
3236 {
3237 t->param = h->param;
3238 memcpy( &t->i_frame, &h->i_frame, offsetof(x264_t, rc) - offsetof(x264_t, i_frame) );
3239 }
3240 int height = h->mb.i_mb_height >> PARAM_INTERLACED;
3241 t->i_threadslice_start = ((height * i + round_bias) / h->param.i_threads) << PARAM_INTERLACED;
3242 t->i_threadslice_end = ((height * (i+1) + round_bias) / h->param.i_threads) << PARAM_INTERLACED;
3243 t->sh.i_first_mb = t->i_threadslice_start * h->mb.i_mb_width;
3244 t->sh.i_last_mb = t->i_threadslice_end * h->mb.i_mb_width - 1;
3245 }
3246
3247 x264_analyse_weight_frame( h, h->mb.i_mb_height*16 + 16 );
3248
3249 x264_threads_distribute_ratecontrol( h );
3250
3251 /* setup */
3252 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
3253 {
3254 h->thread[i]->i_thread_idx = i;
3255 h->thread[i]->b_thread_active = 1;
3256 x264_threadslice_cond_broadcast( h->thread[i], 0 );
3257 }
3258 /* dispatch */
3259 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
3260 x264_threadpool_run( h->threadpool, (void*)slices_write, h->thread[i] );
3261 /* wait */
3262 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
3263 x264_threadslice_cond_wait( h->thread[i], 1 );
3264
3265 x264_threads_merge_ratecontrol( h );
3266
3267 for( int i = 1; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
3268 {
3269 x264_t *t = h->thread[i];
3270 for( int j = 0; j < t->out.i_nal; j++ )
3271 {
3272 h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal] = t->out.nal[j];
3273 h->out.i_nal++;
3274 nal_check_buffer( h );
3275 }
3276 /* All entries in stat.frame are ints except for ssd/ssim. */
3277 for( size_t j = 0; j < (offsetof(x264_t,stat.frame.i_ssd) - offsetof(x264_t,stat.frame.i_mv_bits)) / sizeof(int); j++ )
3278 ((int*)&h->stat.frame)[j] += ((int*)&t->stat.frame)[j];
3279 for( int j = 0; j < 3; j++ )
3280 h->stat.frame.i_ssd[j] += t->stat.frame.i_ssd[j];
3281 h->stat.frame.f_ssim += t->stat.frame.f_ssim;
3282 h->stat.frame.i_ssim_cnt += t->stat.frame.i_ssim_cnt;
3283 }
3284
3285 return 0;
3286}
3287
3288void x264_encoder_intra_refresh( x264_t *h )
3289{
3290 h = h->thread[h->i_thread_phase];
3291 h->b_queued_intra_refresh = 1;
3292}

3294int x264_encoder_invalidate_reference( x264_t *h, int64_t pts )
3295{
3296 if( h->param.i_bframe )
3297 {
3298 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "x264_encoder_invalidate_reference is not supported with B-frames enabled\n" );
3299 return -1;
3300 }
3301 if( h->param.b_intra_refresh )
3302 {
3303 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "x264_encoder_invalidate_reference is not supported with intra refresh enabled\n" );
3304 return -1;
3305 }
3306 h = h->thread[h->i_thread_phase];
3307 if( pts >= h->i_last_idr_pts )
3308 {
3309 for( int i = 0; h->frames.reference[i]; i++ )
3310 if( pts <= h->frames.reference[i]->i_pts )
3311 h->frames.reference[i]->b_corrupt = 1;
3312 if( pts <= h->fdec->i_pts )
3313 h->fdec->b_corrupt = 1;
3314 }
3315 return 0;
3316}

3318/****************************************************************************
3319 * x264_encoder_encode:
3320 * XXX: i_poc : is the poc of the current given picture
3321 * i_frame : is the number of the frame being coded
3322 * ex: type frame poc
3323 * I 0 2*0
3324 * P 1 2*3
3325 * B 2 2*1
3326 * B 3 2*2
3327 * P 4 2*6
3328 * B 5 2*4
3329 * B 6 2*5
3330 ****************************************************************************/
3331int x264_encoder_encode( x264_t *h,
3332 x264_nal_t **pp_nal, int *pi_nal,
3333 x264_picture_t *pic_in,
3334 x264_picture_t *pic_out )
3335{
3336 x264_t *thread_current, *thread_prev, *thread_oldest;
3337 int i_nal_type, i_nal_ref_idc, i_global_qp;
3338 int overhead = NALU_OVERHEAD;
3339
3340#if HAVE_OPENCL
3341 if( h->opencl.b_fatal_error )
3342 return -1;
3343#endif
3344
3345 if( h->i_thread_frames > 1 )
3346 {
3347 thread_prev = h->thread[ h->i_thread_phase ];
3348 h->i_thread_phase = (h->i_thread_phase + 1) % h->i_thread_frames;
3349 thread_current = h->thread[ h->i_thread_phase ];
3350 thread_oldest = h->thread[ (h->i_thread_phase + 1) % h->i_thread_frames ];
3351 thread_sync_context( thread_current, thread_prev );
3352 x264_thread_sync_ratecontrol( thread_current, thread_prev, thread_oldest );
3353 h = thread_current;
3354 }
3355 else
3356 {
3357 thread_current =
3358 thread_oldest = h;
3359 }
3360 h->i_cpb_delay_pir_offset = h->i_cpb_delay_pir_offset_next;
3361
3362 /* no data out */
3363 *pi_nal = 0;
3364 *pp_nal = NULL;
3365
3366 /* ------------------- Setup new frame from picture -------------------- */
3367 if( pic_in != NULL )
3368 {
3369 if( h->lookahead->b_exit_thread )
3370 {
3371 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_ERROR, "lookahead thread is already stopped\n" );
3372 return -1;
3373 }
3374
3375 /* 1: Copy the picture to a frame and move it to a buffer */
3376 x264_frame_t *fenc = x264_frame_pop_unused( h, 0 );
3377 if( !fenc )
3378 return -1;
3379
3380 if( x264_frame_copy_picture( h, fenc, pic_in ) < 0 )
3381 return -1;
3382
3383 if( h->param.i_width != 16 * h->mb.i_mb_width ||
3384 h->param.i_height != 16 * h->mb.i_mb_height )
3385 x264_frame_expand_border_mod16( h, fenc );
3386
3387 fenc->i_frame = h->frames.i_input++;
3388
3389 if( fenc->i_frame == 0 )
3390 h->frames.i_first_pts = fenc->i_pts;
3391 if( h->frames.i_bframe_delay && fenc->i_frame == h->frames.i_bframe_delay )
3392 h->frames.i_bframe_delay_time = fenc->i_pts - h->frames.i_first_pts;
3393
3394 if( h->param.b_vfr_input && fenc->i_pts <= h->frames.i_largest_pts )
3395 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "non-strictly-monotonic PTS\n" );
3396
3397 h->frames.i_second_largest_pts = h->frames.i_largest_pts;
3398 h->frames.i_largest_pts = fenc->i_pts;
3399
3400 if( (fenc->i_pic_struct < PIC_STRUCT_AUTO) || (fenc->i_pic_struct > PIC_STRUCT_TRIPLE) )
3401 fenc->i_pic_struct = PIC_STRUCT_AUTO;
3402
3403 if( fenc->i_pic_struct == PIC_STRUCT_AUTO )
3404 {
3405#if HAVE_INTERLACED
3406 int b_interlaced = fenc->param ? fenc->param->b_interlaced : h->param.b_interlaced;
3407#else
3408 int b_interlaced = 0;
3409#endif
3410 if( b_interlaced )
3411 {
3412 int b_tff = fenc->param ? fenc->param->b_tff : h->param.b_tff;
3413 fenc->i_pic_struct = b_tff ? PIC_STRUCT_TOP_BOTTOM : PIC_STRUCT_BOTTOM_TOP;
3414 }
3415 else
3416 fenc->i_pic_struct = PIC_STRUCT_PROGRESSIVE;
3417 }
3418
3419 if( h->param.rc.b_mb_tree && h->param.rc.b_stat_read )
3420 {
3421 if( x264_macroblock_tree_read( h, fenc, pic_in->prop.quant_offsets ) )
3422 return -1;
3423 }
3424 else
3425 x264_adaptive_quant_frame( h, fenc, pic_in->prop.quant_offsets );
3426
3427 if( pic_in->prop.quant_offsets_free )
3428 pic_in->prop.quant_offsets_free( pic_in->prop.quant_offsets );
3429
3430 if( h->frames.b_have_lowres )
3431 x264_frame_init_lowres( h, fenc );
3432
3433 /* 2: Place the frame into the queue for its slice type decision */
3434 x264_lookahead_put_frame( h, fenc );
3435
3436 if( h->frames.i_input <= h->frames.i_delay + 1 - h->i_thread_frames )
3437 {
3438 /* Nothing yet to encode, waiting for filling of buffers */
3439 pic_out->i_type = X264_TYPE_AUTO;
3440 return 0;
3441 }
3442 }
3443 else
3444 {
3445 /* signal kills for lookahead thread */
3446 x264_pthread_mutex_lock( &h->lookahead->ifbuf.mutex );
3447 h->lookahead->b_exit_thread = 1;
3448 x264_pthread_cond_broadcast( &h->lookahead->ifbuf.cv_fill );
3449 x264_pthread_mutex_unlock( &h->lookahead->ifbuf.mutex );
3450 }
3451
3452 h->i_frame++;
3453 /* 3: The picture is analyzed in the lookahead */
3454 if( !h->frames.current[0] )
3455 x264_lookahead_get_frames( h );
3456
3457 if( !h->frames.current[0] && x264_lookahead_is_empty( h ) )
3458 return encoder_frame_end( thread_oldest, thread_current, pp_nal, pi_nal, pic_out );
3459
3460 /* ------------------- Get frame to be encoded ------------------------- */
3461 /* 4: get picture to encode */
3462 h->fenc = x264_frame_shift( h->frames.current );
3463
3464 /* If applicable, wait for previous frame reconstruction to finish */
3465 if( h->param.b_sliced_threads )
3466 if( threadpool_wait_all( h ) < 0 )
3467 return -1;
3468
3469 if( h->i_frame == 0 )
3470 h->i_reordered_pts_delay = h->fenc->i_reordered_pts;
3471 if( h->reconfig )
3472 {
3473 x264_encoder_reconfig_apply( h, &h->reconfig_h->param );
3474 h->reconfig = 0;
3475 }
3476 if( h->fenc->param )
3477 {
3478 x264_encoder_reconfig_apply( h, h->fenc->param );
3479 if( h->fenc->param->param_free )
3480 {
3481 x264_param_cleanup( h->fenc->param );
3482 h->fenc->param->param_free( h->fenc->param );
3483 h->fenc->param = NULL;
3484 }
3485 }
3486 x264_ratecontrol_zone_init( h );
3487
3488 // ok to call this before encoding any frames, since the initial values of fdec have b_kept_as_ref=0
3489 if( reference_update( h ) )
3490 return -1;
3491 h->fdec->i_lines_completed = -1;
3492
3493 if( !IS_X264_TYPE_I( h->fenc->i_type ) )
3494 {
3495 int valid_refs_left = 0;
3496 for( int i = 0; h->frames.reference[i]; i++ )
3497 if( !h->frames.reference[i]->b_corrupt )
3498 valid_refs_left++;
3499 /* No valid reference frames left: force an IDR. */
3500 if( !valid_refs_left )
3501 {
3502 h->fenc->b_keyframe = 1;
3503 h->fenc->i_type = X264_TYPE_IDR;
3504 }
3505 }
3506
3507 if( h->fenc->b_keyframe )
3508 {
3509 h->frames.i_last_keyframe = h->fenc->i_frame;
3510 if( h->fenc->i_type == X264_TYPE_IDR )
3511 {
3512 h->i_frame_num = 0;
3513 h->frames.i_last_idr = h->fenc->i_frame;
3514 }
3515 }
3516 h->sh.i_mmco_command_count =
3517 h->sh.i_mmco_remove_from_end = 0;
3518 h->b_ref_reorder[0] =
3519 h->b_ref_reorder[1] = 0;
3520 h->fdec->i_poc =
3521 h->fenc->i_poc = 2 * ( h->fenc->i_frame - X264_MAX( h->frames.i_last_idr, 0 ) );
3522
3523 /* ------------------- Setup frame context ----------------------------- */
3524 /* 5: Init data dependent of frame type */
3525 if( h->fenc->i_type == X264_TYPE_IDR )
3526 {
3527 /* reset ref pictures */
3528 i_nal_type = NAL_SLICE_IDR;
3529 i_nal_ref_idc = NAL_PRIORITY_HIGHEST;
3530 h->sh.i_type = SLICE_TYPE_I;
3531 reference_reset( h );
3532 h->frames.i_poc_last_open_gop = -1;
3533 }
3534 else if( h->fenc->i_type == X264_TYPE_I )
3535 {
3536 i_nal_type = NAL_SLICE;
3537 i_nal_ref_idc = NAL_PRIORITY_HIGH; /* Not completely true but for now it is (as all I/P are kept as ref)*/
3538 h->sh.i_type = SLICE_TYPE_I;
3539 reference_hierarchy_reset( h );
3540 if( h->param.b_open_gop )
3541 h->frames.i_poc_last_open_gop = h->fenc->b_keyframe ? h->fenc->i_poc : -1;
3542 }
3543 else if( h->fenc->i_type == X264_TYPE_P )
3544 {
3545 i_nal_type = NAL_SLICE;
3546 i_nal_ref_idc = NAL_PRIORITY_HIGH; /* Not completely true but for now it is (as all I/P are kept as ref)*/
3547 h->sh.i_type = SLICE_TYPE_P;
3548 reference_hierarchy_reset( h );
3549 h->frames.i_poc_last_open_gop = -1;
3550 }
3551 else if( h->fenc->i_type == X264_TYPE_BREF )
3552 {
3553 i_nal_type = NAL_SLICE;
3554 i_nal_ref_idc = h->param.i_bframe_pyramid == X264_B_PYRAMID_STRICT ? NAL_PRIORITY_LOW : NAL_PRIORITY_HIGH;
3555 h->sh.i_type = SLICE_TYPE_B;
3556 reference_hierarchy_reset( h );
3557 }
3558 else /* B frame */
3559 {
3560 i_nal_type = NAL_SLICE;
3561 i_nal_ref_idc = NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE;
3562 h->sh.i_type = SLICE_TYPE_B;
3563 }
3564
3565 h->fdec->i_type = h->fenc->i_type;
3566 h->fdec->i_frame = h->fenc->i_frame;
3567 h->fenc->b_kept_as_ref =
3568 h->fdec->b_kept_as_ref = i_nal_ref_idc != NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE && h->param.i_keyint_max > 1;
3569
3570 h->fdec->mb_info = h->fenc->mb_info;
3571 h->fdec->mb_info_free = h->fenc->mb_info_free;
3572 h->fenc->mb_info = NULL;
3573 h->fenc->mb_info_free = NULL;
3574
3575 h->fdec->i_pts = h->fenc->i_pts;
3576 if( h->frames.i_bframe_delay )
3577 {
3578 int64_t *prev_reordered_pts = thread_current->frames.i_prev_reordered_pts;
3579 h->fdec->i_dts = h->i_frame > h->frames.i_bframe_delay
3580 ? prev_reordered_pts[ (h->i_frame - h->frames.i_bframe_delay) % h->frames.i_bframe_delay ]
3581 : h->fenc->i_reordered_pts - h->frames.i_bframe_delay_time;
3582 prev_reordered_pts[ h->i_frame % h->frames.i_bframe_delay ] = h->fenc->i_reordered_pts;
3583 }
3584 else
3585 h->fdec->i_dts = h->fenc->i_reordered_pts;

3588

3590 /* build ref list 0/1 */
3591 reference_build_list( h, h->fdec->i_poc );
3592
3593 /* ---------------------- Write the bitstream -------------------------- */
3594 /* Init bitstream context */
3595 if( h->param.b_sliced_threads )
3596 {
3597 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_threads; i++ )
3598 {
3599 bs_init( &h->thread[i]->out.bs, h->thread[i]->out.p_bitstream, h->thread[i]->out.i_bitstream );
3600 h->thread[i]->out.i_nal = 0;
3601 }
3602 }
3603 else
3604 {
3605 bs_init( &h->out.bs, h->out.p_bitstream, h->out.i_bitstream );
3606 h->out.i_nal = 0;
3607 }
3608
3609 if( h->param.b_aud )
3610 {
3611 int pic_type;
3612
3613 if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_I )
3614 pic_type = 0;
3615 else if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_P )
3616 pic_type = 1;
3617 else if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B )
3618 pic_type = 2;
3619 else
3620 pic_type = 7;
3621
3622 nal_start( h, NAL_AUD, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
3623 bs_write( &h->out.bs, 3, pic_type );
3624 bs_rbsp_trailing( &h->out.bs );
3625 bs_flush( &h->out.bs );
3626 if( nal_end( h ) )
3627 return -1;
3628 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + NALU_OVERHEAD;
3629 }
3630
3631 h->i_nal_type = i_nal_type;
3632 h->i_nal_ref_idc = i_nal_ref_idc;
3633
3634 if( h->param.b_intra_refresh )
3635 {
3636 if( IS_X264_TYPE_I( h->fenc->i_type ) )
3637 {
3638 h->fdec->i_frames_since_pir = 0;
3639 h->b_queued_intra_refresh = 0;
3640 /* PIR is currently only supported with ref == 1, so any intra frame effectively refreshes
3641 * the whole frame and counts as an intra refresh. */
3642 h->fdec->f_pir_position = h->mb.i_mb_width;
3643 }
3644 else if( h->fenc->i_type == X264_TYPE_P )
3645 {
3646 int pocdiff = (h->fdec->i_poc - h->fref[0][0]->i_poc)/2;
3647 float increment = X264_MAX( ((float)h->mb.i_mb_width-1) / h->param.i_keyint_max, 1 );
3648 h->fdec->f_pir_position = h->fref[0][0]->f_pir_position;
3649 h->fdec->i_frames_since_pir = h->fref[0][0]->i_frames_since_pir + pocdiff;
3650 if( h->fdec->i_frames_since_pir >= h->param.i_keyint_max ||
3651 (h->b_queued_intra_refresh && h->fdec->f_pir_position + 0.5 >= h->mb.i_mb_width) )
3652 {
3653 h->fdec->f_pir_position = 0;
3654 h->fdec->i_frames_since_pir = 0;
3655 h->b_queued_intra_refresh = 0;
3656 h->fenc->b_keyframe = 1;
3657 }
3658 h->fdec->i_pir_start_col = h->fdec->f_pir_position+0.5;
3659 h->fdec->f_pir_position += increment * pocdiff;
3660 h->fdec->i_pir_end_col = h->fdec->f_pir_position+0.5;
3661 /* If our intra refresh has reached the right side of the frame, we're done. */
3662 if( h->fdec->i_pir_end_col >= h->mb.i_mb_width - 1 )
3663 {
3664 h->fdec->f_pir_position = h->mb.i_mb_width;
3665 h->fdec->i_pir_end_col = h->mb.i_mb_width - 1;
3666 }
3667 }
3668 }
3669
3670 if( h->fenc->b_keyframe )
3671 {
3672 /* Write SPS and PPS */
3673 if( h->param.b_repeat_headers )
3674 {
3675 /* generate sequence parameters */
3676 nal_start( h, NAL_SPS, NAL_PRIORITY_HIGHEST );
3677 x264_sps_write( &h->out.bs, h->sps );
3678 if( nal_end( h ) )
3679 return -1;
3680 /* Pad AUD/SPS to 256 bytes like Panasonic */
3681 if( h->param.i_avcintra_class )
3682 h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_padding = 256 - bs_pos( &h->out.bs ) / 8 - 2*NALU_OVERHEAD;
3683 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_padding + NALU_OVERHEAD;
3684
3685 /* generate picture parameters */
3686 nal_start( h, NAL_PPS, NAL_PRIORITY_HIGHEST );
3687 x264_pps_write( &h->out.bs, h->sps, h->pps );
3688 if( nal_end( h ) )
3689 return -1;
3690 if( h->param.i_avcintra_class )
3691 {
3692 int total_len = 256;
3693 /* Sony XAVC uses an oversized PPS instead of SEI padding */
3694 if( h->param.i_avcintra_flavor == X264_AVCINTRA_FLAVOR_SONY )
3695 total_len += h->param.i_height >= 1080 ? 18*512 : 10*512;
3696 h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_padding = total_len - h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload - NALU_OVERHEAD;
3697 }
3698 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_padding + NALU_OVERHEAD;
3699 }
3700
3701 /* when frame threading is used, buffering period sei is written in encoder_frame_end */
3702 if( h->i_thread_frames == 1 && h->sps->vui.b_nal_hrd_parameters_present )
3703 {
3704 x264_hrd_fullness( h );
3705 nal_start( h, NAL_SEI, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
3706 x264_sei_buffering_period_write( h, &h->out.bs );
3707 if( nal_end( h ) )
3708 return -1;
3709 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + SEI_OVERHEAD;
3710 }
3711 }
3712
3713 /* write extra sei */
3714 for( int i = 0; i < h->fenc->extra_sei.num_payloads; i++ )
3715 {
3716 nal_start( h, NAL_SEI, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
3717 x264_sei_write( &h->out.bs, h->fenc->extra_sei.payloads[i].payload, h->fenc->extra_sei.payloads[i].payload_size,
3718 h->fenc->extra_sei.payloads[i].payload_type );
3719 if( nal_end( h ) )
3720 return -1;
3721 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + SEI_OVERHEAD;
3722 if( h->fenc->extra_sei.sei_free )
3723 {
3724 h->fenc->extra_sei.sei_free( h->fenc->extra_sei.payloads[i].payload );
3725 h->fenc->extra_sei.payloads[i].payload = NULL;
3726 }
3727 }
3728
3729 if( h->fenc->extra_sei.sei_free )
3730 {
3731 h->fenc->extra_sei.sei_free( h->fenc->extra_sei.payloads );
3732 h->fenc->extra_sei.payloads = NULL;
3733 h->fenc->extra_sei.sei_free = NULL;
3734 }
3735
3736 if( h->fenc->b_keyframe )
3737 {
3738 /* Avid's decoder strictly wants two SEIs for AVC-Intra so we can't insert the x264 SEI */
3739 if( h->param.b_repeat_headers && h->fenc->i_frame == 0 && !h->param.i_avcintra_class )
3740 {
3741 /* identify ourself */
3742 nal_start( h, NAL_SEI, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
3743 if( x264_sei_version_write( h, &h->out.bs ) )
3744 return -1;
3745 if( nal_end( h ) )
3746 return -1;
3747 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + SEI_OVERHEAD;
3748 }
3749
3750 if( h->fenc->i_type != X264_TYPE_IDR )
3751 {
3752 int time_to_recovery = h->param.b_open_gop ? 0 : X264_MIN( h->mb.i_mb_width - 1, h->param.i_keyint_max ) + h->param.i_bframe - 1;
3753 nal_start( h, NAL_SEI, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
3754 x264_sei_recovery_point_write( h, &h->out.bs, time_to_recovery );
3755 if( nal_end( h ) )
3756 return -1;
3757 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + SEI_OVERHEAD;
3758 }
3759
3760 if( h->param.mastering_display.b_mastering_display )
3761 {
3762 nal_start( h, NAL_SEI, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
3763 x264_sei_mastering_display_write( h, &h->out.bs );
3764 if( nal_end( h ) )
3765 return -1;
3766 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + SEI_OVERHEAD;
3767 }
3768
3769 if( h->param.content_light_level.b_cll )
3770 {
3771 nal_start( h, NAL_SEI, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
3772 x264_sei_content_light_level_write( h, &h->out.bs );
3773 if( nal_end( h ) )
3774 return -1;
3775 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + SEI_OVERHEAD;
3776 }
3777
3778 if( h->param.i_alternative_transfer != 2 )
3779 {
3780 nal_start( h, NAL_SEI, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
3781 x264_sei_alternative_transfer_write( h, &h->out.bs );
3782 if( nal_end( h ) )
3783 return -1;
3784 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + SEI_OVERHEAD;
3785 }
3786 }
3787
3788 if( h->param.i_frame_packing >= 0 && (h->fenc->b_keyframe || h->param.i_frame_packing == 5) )
3789 {
3790 nal_start( h, NAL_SEI, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
3791 x264_sei_frame_packing_write( h, &h->out.bs );
3792 if( nal_end( h ) )
3793 return -1;
3794 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + SEI_OVERHEAD;
3795 }
3796
3797 /* generate sei pic timing */
3798 if( h->sps->vui.b_pic_struct_present || h->sps->vui.b_nal_hrd_parameters_present )
3799 {
3800 nal_start( h, NAL_SEI, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
3801 x264_sei_pic_timing_write( h, &h->out.bs );
3802 if( nal_end( h ) )
3803 return -1;
3804 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + SEI_OVERHEAD;
3805 }
3806
3807 /* As required by Blu-ray. */
3808 if( !IS_X264_TYPE_B( h->fenc->i_type ) && h->b_sh_backup )
3809 {
3810 h->b_sh_backup = 0;
3811 nal_start( h, NAL_SEI, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
3812 x264_sei_dec_ref_pic_marking_write( h, &h->out.bs );
3813 if( nal_end( h ) )
3814 return -1;
3815 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + SEI_OVERHEAD;
3816 }
3817
3818 if( h->fenc->b_keyframe && h->param.b_intra_refresh )
3819 h->i_cpb_delay_pir_offset_next = h->fenc->i_cpb_delay;
3820
3821 /* Filler space: 10 or 18 SEIs' worth of space, depending on resolution */
3822 if( h->param.i_avcintra_class && h->param.i_avcintra_flavor != X264_AVCINTRA_FLAVOR_SONY )
3823 {
3824 /* Write an empty filler NAL to mimic the AUD in the P2 format*/
3825 nal_start( h, NAL_FILLER, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
3826 x264_filler_write( h, &h->out.bs, 0 );
3827 if( nal_end( h ) )
3828 return -1;
3829 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + NALU_OVERHEAD;
3830
3831 /* All lengths are magic lengths that decoders expect to see */
3832 /* "UMID" SEI */
3833 nal_start( h, NAL_SEI, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
3834 if( x264_sei_avcintra_umid_write( h, &h->out.bs ) < 0 )
3835 return -1;
3836 if( nal_end( h ) )
3837 return -1;
3838 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + SEI_OVERHEAD;
3839
3840 int unpadded_len;
3841 int total_len;
3842 if( h->param.i_height == 1080 )
3843 {
3844 unpadded_len = 5780;
3845 total_len = 17*512;
3846 }
3847 else
3848 {
3849 unpadded_len = 2900;
3850 total_len = 9*512;
3851 }
3852 /* "VANC" SEI */
3853 nal_start( h, NAL_SEI, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
3854 if( x264_sei_avcintra_vanc_write( h, &h->out.bs, unpadded_len ) < 0 )
3855 return -1;
3856 if( nal_end( h ) )
3857 return -1;
3858
3859 h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_padding = total_len - h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload - SEI_OVERHEAD;
3860 overhead += h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_payload + h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1].i_padding + SEI_OVERHEAD;
3861 }
3862
3863 /* Init the rate control */
3864 /* FIXME: Include slice header bit cost. */
3865 x264_ratecontrol_start( h, h->fenc->i_qpplus1, overhead*8 );
3866 i_global_qp = x264_ratecontrol_qp( h );
3867
3868 pic_out->i_qpplus1 =
3869 h->fdec->i_qpplus1 = i_global_qp + 1;
3870
3871 if( h->param.rc.b_stat_read && h->sh.i_type != SLICE_TYPE_I )
3872 {
3873 x264_reference_build_list_optimal( h );
3874 reference_check_reorder( h );
3875 }
3876
3877 if( h->i_ref[0] )
3878 h->fdec->i_poc_l0ref0 = h->fref[0][0]->i_poc;
3879
3880 /* ------------------------ Create slice header ----------------------- */
3881 slice_init( h, i_nal_type, i_global_qp );
3882
3883 /*------------------------- Weights -------------------------------------*/
3884 if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B )
3885 x264_macroblock_bipred_init( h );
3886
3887 weighted_pred_init( h );
3888
3889 if( i_nal_ref_idc != NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE )
3890 h->i_frame_num++;
3891
3892 /* Write frame */
3893 h->i_threadslice_start = 0;
3894 h->i_threadslice_end = h->mb.i_mb_height;
3895 if( h->i_thread_frames > 1 )
3896 {
3897 x264_threadpool_run( h->threadpool, (void*)slices_write, h );
3898 h->b_thread_active = 1;
3899 }
3900 else if( h->param.b_sliced_threads )
3901 {
3902 if( threaded_slices_write( h ) )
3903 return -1;
3904 }
3905 else
3906 if( (intptr_t)slices_write( h ) )
3907 return -1;
3908
3909 return encoder_frame_end( thread_oldest, thread_current, pp_nal, pi_nal, pic_out );
3910}
3911
3912static int encoder_frame_end( x264_t *h, x264_t *thread_current,
3913 x264_nal_t **pp_nal, int *pi_nal,
3914 x264_picture_t *pic_out )
3915{
3916 char psz_message[80];
3917
3918 if( !h->param.b_sliced_threads && h->b_thread_active )
3919 {
3920 h->b_thread_active = 0;
3921 if( (intptr_t)x264_threadpool_wait( h->threadpool, h ) )
3922 return -1;
3923 }
3924 if( !h->out.i_nal )
3925 {
3926 pic_out->i_type = X264_TYPE_AUTO;
3927 return 0;
3928 }
3929
3930 x264_emms();
3931
3932 /* generate buffering period sei and insert it into place */
3933 if( h->i_thread_frames > 1 && h->fenc->b_keyframe && h->sps->vui.b_nal_hrd_parameters_present )
3934 {
3935 x264_hrd_fullness( h );
3936 nal_start( h, NAL_SEI, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
3937 x264_sei_buffering_period_write( h, &h->out.bs );
3938 if( nal_end( h ) )
3939 return -1;
3940 /* buffering period sei must follow AUD, SPS and PPS and precede all other SEIs */
3941 int idx = 0;
3942 while( h->out.nal[idx].i_type == NAL_AUD ||
3943 h->out.nal[idx].i_type == NAL_SPS ||
3944 h->out.nal[idx].i_type == NAL_PPS )
3945 idx++;
3946 x264_nal_t nal_tmp = h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1];
3947 memmove( &h->out.nal[idx+1], &h->out.nal[idx], (h->out.i_nal-idx-1)*sizeof(x264_nal_t) );
3948 h->out.nal[idx] = nal_tmp;
3949 }
3950
3951 int frame_size = encoder_encapsulate_nals( h, 0 );
3952 if( frame_size < 0 )
3953 return -1;
3954
3955 /* Set output picture properties */
3956 pic_out->i_type = h->fenc->i_type;
3957
3958 pic_out->b_keyframe = h->fenc->b_keyframe;
3959 pic_out->i_pic_struct = h->fenc->i_pic_struct;
3960
3961 pic_out->i_pts = h->fdec->i_pts;
3962 pic_out->i_dts = h->fdec->i_dts;
3963
3964 if( pic_out->i_pts < pic_out->i_dts )
3965 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_WARNING, "invalid DTS: PTS is less than DTS\n" );
3966
3967 pic_out->opaque = h->fenc->opaque;
3968
3969 pic_out->img.i_csp = h->fdec->i_csp;
3970#if HIGH_BIT_DEPTH
3971 pic_out->img.i_csp |= X264_CSP_HIGH_DEPTH;
3972#endif
3973 pic_out->img.i_plane = h->fdec->i_plane;
3974 for( int i = 0; i < pic_out->img.i_plane; i++ )
3975 {
3976 pic_out->img.i_stride[i] = h->fdec->i_stride[i] * SIZEOF_PIXEL;
3977 pic_out->img.plane[i] = (uint8_t*)h->fdec->plane[i];
3978 }
3979
3980 x264_frame_push_unused( thread_current, h->fenc );
3981
3982 /* ---------------------- Update encoder state ------------------------- */
3983
3984 /* update rc */
3985 int filler = 0;
3986 if( x264_ratecontrol_end( h, frame_size * 8, &filler ) < 0 )
3987 return -1;
3988
3989 pic_out->hrd_timing = h->fenc->hrd_timing;
3990 pic_out->prop.f_crf_avg = h->fdec->f_crf_avg;
3991
3992 /* Filler in AVC-Intra mode is written as zero bytes to the last slice
3993 * We don't know the size of the last slice until encapsulation so we add filler to the encapsulated NAL */
3994 if( h->param.i_avcintra_class )
3995 {
3996 if( check_encapsulated_buffer( h, h->thread[0], h->out.i_nal, frame_size, (int64_t)frame_size + filler ) < 0 )
3997 return -1;
3998
3999 x264_nal_t *nal = &h->out.nal[h->out.i_nal-1];
4000 memset( nal->p_payload + nal->i_payload, 0, filler );
4001 nal->i_payload += filler;
4002 nal->i_padding = filler;
4003 frame_size += filler;
4004
4005 /* Fix up the size header for mp4/etc */
4006 if( !h->param.b_annexb )
4007 {
4008 /* Size doesn't include the size of the header we're writing now. */
4009 uint8_t *nal_data = nal->p_payload;
4010 int chunk_size = nal->i_payload - 4;
4011 nal_data[0] = chunk_size >> 24;
4012 nal_data[1] = chunk_size >> 16;
4013 nal_data[2] = chunk_size >> 8;
4014 nal_data[3] = chunk_size >> 0;
4015 }
4016 }
4017 else
4018 {
4019 while( filler > 0 )
4020 {
4021 int f, overhead = FILLER_OVERHEAD - h->param.b_annexb;
4022 if( h->param.i_slice_max_size && filler > h->param.i_slice_max_size )
4023 {
4024 int next_size = filler - h->param.i_slice_max_size;
4025 int overflow = X264_MAX( overhead - next_size, 0 );
4026 f = h->param.i_slice_max_size - overhead - overflow;
4027 }
4028 else
4029 f = X264_MAX( 0, filler - overhead );
4030
4031 if( bitstream_check_buffer_filler( h, f ) )
4032 return -1;
4033 nal_start( h, NAL_FILLER, NAL_PRIORITY_DISPOSABLE );
4034 x264_filler_write( h, &h->out.bs, f );
4035 if( nal_end( h ) )
4036 return -1;
4037 int total_size = encoder_encapsulate_nals( h, h->out.i_nal-1 );
4038 if( total_size < 0 )
4039 return -1;
4040 frame_size += total_size;
4041 filler -= total_size;
4042 }
4043 }
4044
4045 /* End bitstream, set output */
4046 *pi_nal = h->out.i_nal;
4047 *pp_nal = h->out.nal;
4048
4049 h->out.i_nal = 0;
4050
4051 x264_noise_reduction_update( h );
4052
4053 /* ---------------------- Compute/Print statistics --------------------- */
4054 thread_sync_stat( h, h->thread[0] );
4055
4056 /* Slice stat */
4057 h->stat.i_frame_count[h->sh.i_type]++;
4058 h->stat.i_frame_size[h->sh.i_type] += frame_size;
4059 h->stat.f_frame_qp[h->sh.i_type] += h->fdec->f_qp_avg_aq;
4060
4061 for( int i = 0; i < X264_MBTYPE_MAX; i++ )
4062 h->stat.i_mb_count[h->sh.i_type][i] += h->stat.frame.i_mb_count[i];
4063 for( int i = 0; i < 2; i++ )
4064 h->stat.i_mb_count_8x8dct[i] += h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_8x8dct[i];
4065 for( int i = 0; i < 6; i++ )
4066 h->stat.i_mb_cbp[i] += h->stat.frame.i_mb_cbp[i];
4067 for( int i = 0; i < 4; i++ )
4068 for( int j = 0; j < 13; j++ )
4069 h->stat.i_mb_pred_mode[i][j] += h->stat.frame.i_mb_pred_mode[i][j];
4070 if( h->sh.i_type != SLICE_TYPE_I )
4071 {
4072 for( int i = 0; i < X264_PARTTYPE_MAX; i++ )
4073 h->stat.i_mb_partition[h->sh.i_type][i] += h->stat.frame.i_mb_partition[i];
4074 for( int i_list = 0; i_list < 2; i_list++ )
4075 for( int i = 0; i < X264_REF_MAX*2; i++ )
4076 h->stat.i_mb_count_ref[h->sh.i_type][i_list][i] += h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_ref[i_list][i];
4077 }
4078 for( int i = 0; i < 3; i++ )
4079 h->stat.i_mb_field[i] += h->stat.frame.i_mb_field[i];
4080 if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_P && h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred >= X264_WEIGHTP_SIMPLE )
4081 {
4082 h->stat.i_wpred[0] += !!h->sh.weight[0][0].weightfn;
4083 h->stat.i_wpred[1] += !!h->sh.weight[0][1].weightfn || !!h->sh.weight[0][2].weightfn;
4084 }
4085 if( h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_B )
4086 {
4087 h->stat.i_direct_frames[ h->sh.b_direct_spatial_mv_pred ] ++;
4088 if( h->mb.b_direct_auto_write )
4089 {
4090 //FIXME somewhat arbitrary time constants
4091 if( h->stat.i_direct_score[0] + h->stat.i_direct_score[1] > h->mb.i_mb_count )
4092 for( int i = 0; i < 2; i++ )
4093 h->stat.i_direct_score[i] = h->stat.i_direct_score[i] * 9/10;
4094 for( int i = 0; i < 2; i++ )
4095 h->stat.i_direct_score[i] += h->stat.frame.i_direct_score[i];
4096 }
4097 }
4098 else
4099 h->stat.i_consecutive_bframes[h->fenc->i_bframes]++;
4100
4101 psz_message[0] = '\0';
4102 double dur = h->fenc->f_duration;
4103 h->stat.f_frame_duration[h->sh.i_type] += dur;
4104 if( h->param.analyse.b_psnr )
4105 {
4106 int64_t ssd[3] =
4107 {
4108 h->stat.frame.i_ssd[0],
4109 h->stat.frame.i_ssd[1],
4110 h->stat.frame.i_ssd[2],
4111 };
4112 int luma_size = h->param.i_width * h->param.i_height;
4113 int chroma_size = CHROMA_SIZE( luma_size );
4114 pic_out->prop.f_psnr[0] = calc_psnr( ssd[0], luma_size );
4115 pic_out->prop.f_psnr[1] = calc_psnr( ssd[1], chroma_size );
4116 pic_out->prop.f_psnr[2] = calc_psnr( ssd[2], chroma_size );
4117 pic_out->prop.f_psnr_avg = calc_psnr( ssd[0] + ssd[1] + ssd[2], luma_size + chroma_size*2 );
4118
4119 h->stat.f_ssd_global[h->sh.i_type] += dur * (ssd[0] + ssd[1] + ssd[2]);
4120 h->stat.f_psnr_average[h->sh.i_type] += dur * pic_out->prop.f_psnr_avg;
4121 h->stat.f_psnr_mean_y[h->sh.i_type] += dur * pic_out->prop.f_psnr[0];
4122 h->stat.f_psnr_mean_u[h->sh.i_type] += dur * pic_out->prop.f_psnr[1];
4123 h->stat.f_psnr_mean_v[h->sh.i_type] += dur * pic_out->prop.f_psnr[2];
4124
4125 snprintf( psz_message, 80, " PSNR Y:%5.2f U:%5.2f V:%5.2f", pic_out->prop.f_psnr[0],
4126 pic_out->prop.f_psnr[1],
4127 pic_out->prop.f_psnr[2] );
4128 }
4129
4130 if( h->param.analyse.b_ssim )
4131 {
4132 pic_out->prop.f_ssim = h->stat.frame.f_ssim / h->stat.frame.i_ssim_cnt;
4133 h->stat.f_ssim_mean_y[h->sh.i_type] += pic_out->prop.f_ssim * dur;
4134 int msg_len = strlen(psz_message);
4135 snprintf( psz_message + msg_len, 80 - msg_len, " SSIM Y:%.5f", pic_out->prop.f_ssim );
4136 }
4137 psz_message[79] = '\0';
4138
4139 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_DEBUG,
4140 "frame=%4d QP=%.2f NAL=%d Slice:%c Poc:%-3d I:%-4d P:%-4d SKIP:%-4d size=%d bytes%s\n",
4141 h->i_frame,
4142 h->fdec->f_qp_avg_aq,
4143 h->i_nal_ref_idc,
4144 h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_I ? 'I' : (h->sh.i_type == SLICE_TYPE_P ? 'P' : 'B' ),
4145 h->fdec->i_poc,
4146 h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_i,
4147 h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_p,
4148 h->stat.frame.i_mb_count_skip,
4149 frame_size,
4150 psz_message );
4151
4152 // keep stats all in one place
4153 thread_sync_stat( h->thread[0], h );
4154 // for the use of the next frame
4155 thread_sync_stat( thread_current, h );
4156
4157#ifdef DEBUG_MB_TYPE
4158{
4159 static const char mb_chars[] = { 'i', 'i', 'I', 'C', 'P', '8', 'S',
4160 'D', '<', 'X', 'B', 'X', '>', 'B', 'B', 'B', 'B', '8', 'S' };
4161 for( int mb_xy = 0; mb_xy < h->mb.i_mb_width * h->mb.i_mb_height; mb_xy++ )
4162 {
4163 if( h->mb.type[mb_xy] < X264_MBTYPE_MAX && h->mb.type[mb_xy] >= 0 )
4164 fprintf( stderr, "%c ", mb_chars[ h->mb.type[mb_xy] ] );
4165 else
4166 fprintf( stderr, "? " );
4167
4168 if( (mb_xy+1) % h->mb.i_mb_width == 0 )
4169 fprintf( stderr, "\n" );
4170 }
4171}
4172#endif
4173
4174 /* Remove duplicates, must be done near the end as breaks h->fref0 array
4175 * by freeing some of its pointers. */
4176 for( int i = 0; i < h->i_ref[0]; i++ )
4177 if( h->fref[0][i] && h->fref[0][i]->b_duplicate )
4178 {
4179 x264_frame_push_blank_unused( h, h->fref[0][i] );
4180 h->fref[0][i] = 0;
4181 }
4182
4183 if( h->param.psz_dump_yuv )
4184 frame_dump( h );
4185 x264_emms();
4186
4187 return frame_size;
4188}
4189
4190static void print_intra( int64_t *i_mb_count, double i_count, int b_print_pcm, char *intra )
4191{
4192 intra += sprintf( intra, "I16..4%s: %4.1f%% %4.1f%% %4.1f%%",
4193 b_print_pcm ? "..PCM" : "",
4194 i_mb_count[I_16x16]/ i_count,
4195 i_mb_count[I_8x8] / i_count,
4196 i_mb_count[I_4x4] / i_count );
4197 if( b_print_pcm )
4198 sprintf( intra, " %4.1f%%", i_mb_count[I_PCM] / i_count );
4199}

4201/****************************************************************************
4202 * x264_encoder_close:
4203 ****************************************************************************/
4204void x264_encoder_close ( x264_t *h )
4205{
4206 int64_t i_yuv_size = FRAME_SIZE( h->param.i_width * h->param.i_height );
4207 int64_t i_mb_count_size[2][7] = {{0}};
4208 char buf[200];
4209 int b_print_pcm = h->stat.i_mb_count[SLICE_TYPE_I][I_PCM]
4210 || h->stat.i_mb_count[SLICE_TYPE_P][I_PCM]
4211 || h->stat.i_mb_count[SLICE_TYPE_B][I_PCM];
4212
4213 x264_lookahead_delete( h );
4214
4215#if HAVE_OPENCL
4216 x264_opencl_lookahead_delete( h );
4217 x264_opencl_function_t *ocl = h->opencl.ocl;
4218#endif
4219
4220 if( h->param.b_sliced_threads )
4221 threadpool_wait_all( h );
4222 if( h->param.i_threads > 1 )
4223 x264_threadpool_delete( h->threadpool );
4224 if( h->param.i_lookahead_threads > 1 )
4225 x264_threadpool_delete( h->lookaheadpool );
4226 if( h->i_thread_frames > 1 )
4227 {
4228 for( int i = 0; i < h->i_thread_frames; i++ )
4229 if( h->thread[i]->b_thread_active )
4230 {
4231 assert( h->thread[i]->fenc->i_reference_count == 1 );
4232 x264_frame_delete( h->thread[i]->fenc );
4233 }
4234
4235 x264_t *thread_prev = h->thread[h->i_thread_phase];
4236 x264_thread_sync_ratecontrol( h, thread_prev, h );
4237 x264_thread_sync_ratecontrol( thread_prev, thread_prev, h );
4238 h->i_frame = thread_prev->i_frame + 1 - h->i_thread_frames;
4239 }
4240 h->i_frame++;
4241
4242 /* Slices used and PSNR */
4243 for( int i = 0; i < 3; i++ )
4244 {
4245 static const uint8_t slice_order[] = { SLICE_TYPE_I, SLICE_TYPE_P, SLICE_TYPE_B };
4246 int i_slice = slice_order[i];
4247
4248 if( h->stat.i_frame_count[i_slice] > 0 )
4249 {
4250 int i_count = h->stat.i_frame_count[i_slice];
4251 double dur = h->stat.f_frame_duration[i_slice];
4252 if( h->param.analyse.b_psnr )
4253 {
4254 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO,
4255 "frame %c:%-5d Avg QP:%5.2f size:%6.0f PSNR Mean Y:%5.2f U:%5.2f V:%5.2f Avg:%5.2f Global:%5.2f\n",
4256 slice_type_to_char[i_slice],
4257 i_count,
4258 h->stat.f_frame_qp[i_slice] / i_count,
4259 (double)h->stat.i_frame_size[i_slice] / i_count,
4260 h->stat.f_psnr_mean_y[i_slice] / dur, h->stat.f_psnr_mean_u[i_slice] / dur, h->stat.f_psnr_mean_v[i_slice] / dur,
4261 h->stat.f_psnr_average[i_slice] / dur,
4262 calc_psnr( h->stat.f_ssd_global[i_slice], dur * i_yuv_size ) );
4263 }
4264 else
4265 {
4266 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO,
4267 "frame %c:%-5d Avg QP:%5.2f size:%6.0f\n",
4268 slice_type_to_char[i_slice],
4269 i_count,
4270 h->stat.f_frame_qp[i_slice] / i_count,
4271 (double)h->stat.i_frame_size[i_slice] / i_count );
4272 }
4273 }
4274 }
4275 if( h->param.i_bframe && h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_B] )
4276 {
4277 char *p = buf;
4278 int den = 0;
4279 // weight by number of frames (including the I/P-frames) that are in a sequence of N B-frames
4280 for( int i = 0; i <= h->param.i_bframe; i++ )
4281 den += (i+1) * h->stat.i_consecutive_bframes[i];
4282 for( int i = 0; i <= h->param.i_bframe; i++ )
4283 p += sprintf( p, " %4.1f%%", 100. * (i+1) * h->stat.i_consecutive_bframes[i] / den );
4284 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "consecutive B-frames:%s\n", buf );
4285 }
4286
4287 for( int i_type = 0; i_type < 2; i_type++ )
4288 for( int i = 0; i < X264_PARTTYPE_MAX; i++ )
4289 {
4290 if( i == D_DIRECT_8x8 ) continue; /* direct is counted as its own type */
4291 i_mb_count_size[i_type][x264_mb_partition_pixel_table[i]] += h->stat.i_mb_partition[i_type][i];
4292 }
4293
4294 /* MB types used */
4295 if( h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_I] > 0 )
4296 {
4297 int64_t *i_mb_count = h->stat.i_mb_count[SLICE_TYPE_I];
4298 double i_count = (double)h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_I] * h->mb.i_mb_count / 100.0;
4299 print_intra( i_mb_count, i_count, b_print_pcm, buf );
4300 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "mb I %s\n", buf );
4301 }
4302 if( h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_P] > 0 )
4303 {
4304 int64_t *i_mb_count = h->stat.i_mb_count[SLICE_TYPE_P];
4305 double i_count = (double)h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_P] * h->mb.i_mb_count / 100.0;
4306 int64_t *i_mb_size = i_mb_count_size[SLICE_TYPE_P];
4307 print_intra( i_mb_count, i_count, b_print_pcm, buf );
4308 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO,
4309 "mb P %s P16..4: %4.1f%% %4.1f%% %4.1f%% %4.1f%% %4.1f%% skip:%4.1f%%\n",
4310 buf,
4311 i_mb_size[PIXEL_16x16] / (i_count*4),
4312 (i_mb_size[PIXEL_16x8] + i_mb_size[PIXEL_8x16]) / (i_count*4),
4313 i_mb_size[PIXEL_8x8] / (i_count*4),
4314 (i_mb_size[PIXEL_8x4] + i_mb_size[PIXEL_4x8]) / (i_count*4),
4315 i_mb_size[PIXEL_4x4] / (i_count*4),
4316 i_mb_count[P_SKIP] / i_count );
4317 }
4318 if( h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_B] > 0 )
4319 {
4320 int64_t *i_mb_count = h->stat.i_mb_count[SLICE_TYPE_B];
4321 double i_count = (double)h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_B] * h->mb.i_mb_count / 100.0;
4322 double i_mb_list_count;
4323 int64_t *i_mb_size = i_mb_count_size[SLICE_TYPE_B];
4324 int64_t list_count[3] = {0}; /* 0 == L0, 1 == L1, 2 == BI */
4325 print_intra( i_mb_count, i_count, b_print_pcm, buf );
4326 for( int i = 0; i < X264_PARTTYPE_MAX; i++ )
4327 for( int j = 0; j < 2; j++ )
4328 {
4329 int l0 = x264_mb_type_list_table[i][0][j];
4330 int l1 = x264_mb_type_list_table[i][1][j];
4331 if( l0 || l1 )
4332 list_count[l1+l0*l1] += h->stat.i_mb_count[SLICE_TYPE_B][i] * 2;
4333 }
4334 list_count[0] += h->stat.i_mb_partition[SLICE_TYPE_B][D_L0_8x8];
4335 list_count[1] += h->stat.i_mb_partition[SLICE_TYPE_B][D_L1_8x8];
4336 list_count[2] += h->stat.i_mb_partition[SLICE_TYPE_B][D_BI_8x8];
4337 i_mb_count[B_DIRECT] += (h->stat.i_mb_partition[SLICE_TYPE_B][D_DIRECT_8x8]+2)/4;
4338 i_mb_list_count = (list_count[0] + list_count[1] + list_count[2]) / 100.0;
4339 sprintf( buf + strlen(buf), " B16..8: %4.1f%% %4.1f%% %4.1f%% direct:%4.1f%% skip:%4.1f%%",
4340 i_mb_size[PIXEL_16x16] / (i_count*4),
4341 (i_mb_size[PIXEL_16x8] + i_mb_size[PIXEL_8x16]) / (i_count*4),
4342 i_mb_size[PIXEL_8x8] / (i_count*4),
4343 i_mb_count[B_DIRECT] / i_count,
4344 i_mb_count[B_SKIP] / i_count );
4345 if( i_mb_list_count != 0 )
4346 sprintf( buf + strlen(buf), " L0:%4.1f%% L1:%4.1f%% BI:%4.1f%%",
4347 list_count[0] / i_mb_list_count,
4348 list_count[1] / i_mb_list_count,
4349 list_count[2] / i_mb_list_count );
4350 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "mb B %s\n", buf );
4351 }
4352
4353 x264_ratecontrol_summary( h );
4354
4355 if( h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_I] + h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_P] + h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_B] > 0 )
4356 {
4357#define SUM3(p) (p[SLICE_TYPE_I] + p[SLICE_TYPE_P] + p[SLICE_TYPE_B])
4358#define SUM3b(p,o) (p[SLICE_TYPE_I][o] + p[SLICE_TYPE_P][o] + p[SLICE_TYPE_B][o])
4359 int64_t i_i8x8 = SUM3b( h->stat.i_mb_count, I_8x8 );
4360 int64_t i_intra = i_i8x8 + SUM3b( h->stat.i_mb_count, I_4x4 )
4361 + SUM3b( h->stat.i_mb_count, I_16x16 );
4362 int64_t i_all_intra = i_intra + SUM3b( h->stat.i_mb_count, I_PCM );
4363 int64_t i_skip = SUM3b( h->stat.i_mb_count, P_SKIP )
4364 + SUM3b( h->stat.i_mb_count, B_SKIP );
4365 const int i_count = h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_I] +
4366 h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_P] +
4367 h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_B];
4368 int64_t i_mb_count = (int64_t)i_count * h->mb.i_mb_count;
4369 int64_t i_inter = i_mb_count - i_skip - i_all_intra;
4370 const double duration = h->stat.f_frame_duration[SLICE_TYPE_I] +
4371 h->stat.f_frame_duration[SLICE_TYPE_P] +
4372 h->stat.f_frame_duration[SLICE_TYPE_B];
4373 float f_bitrate = SUM3(h->stat.i_frame_size) / duration / 125;
4374
4375 if( PARAM_INTERLACED )
4376 {
4377 char *fieldstats = buf;
4378 fieldstats[0] = 0;
4379 if( i_inter )
4380 fieldstats += sprintf( fieldstats, " inter:%.1f%%", h->stat.i_mb_field[1] * 100.0 / i_inter );
4381 if( i_skip )
4382 fieldstats += sprintf( fieldstats, " skip:%.1f%%", h->stat.i_mb_field[2] * 100.0 / i_skip );
4383 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "field mbs: intra: %.1f%%%s\n",
4384 h->stat.i_mb_field[0] * 100.0 / i_all_intra, buf );
4385 }
4386
4387 if( h->pps->b_transform_8x8_mode )
4388 {
4389 buf[0] = 0;
4390 if( h->stat.i_mb_count_8x8dct[0] )
4391 sprintf( buf, " inter:%.1f%%", 100. * h->stat.i_mb_count_8x8dct[1] / h->stat.i_mb_count_8x8dct[0] );
4392 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "8x8 transform intra:%.1f%%%s\n", 100. * i_i8x8 / X264_MAX( i_intra, 1 ), buf );
4393 }
4394
4395 if( (h->param.analyse.i_direct_mv_pred == X264_DIRECT_PRED_AUTO ||
4396 (h->stat.i_direct_frames[0] && h->stat.i_direct_frames[1]))
4397 && h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_B] )
4398 {
4399 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "direct mvs spatial:%.1f%% temporal:%.1f%%\n",
4400 h->stat.i_direct_frames[1] * 100. / h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_B],
4401 h->stat.i_direct_frames[0] * 100. / h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_B] );
4402 }
4403
4404 buf[0] = 0;
4405 if( CHROMA_FORMAT )
4406 {
4407 int csize = CHROMA444 ? 4 : 1;
4408 if( i_mb_count != i_all_intra )
4409 sprintf( buf, " inter: %.1f%% %.1f%% %.1f%%",
4410 h->stat.i_mb_cbp[1] * 100.0 / ((i_mb_count - i_all_intra)*4),
4411 h->stat.i_mb_cbp[3] * 100.0 / ((i_mb_count - i_all_intra)*csize),
4412 h->stat.i_mb_cbp[5] * 100.0 / ((i_mb_count - i_all_intra)*csize) );
4413 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "coded y,%s,%s intra: %.1f%% %.1f%% %.1f%%%s\n",
4414 CHROMA444?"u":"uvDC", CHROMA444?"v":"uvAC",
4415 h->stat.i_mb_cbp[0] * 100.0 / (i_all_intra*4),
4416 h->stat.i_mb_cbp[2] * 100.0 / (i_all_intra*csize),
4417 h->stat.i_mb_cbp[4] * 100.0 / (i_all_intra*csize), buf );
4418 }
4419 else
4420 {
4421 if( i_mb_count != i_all_intra )
4422 sprintf( buf, " inter: %.1f%%", h->stat.i_mb_cbp[1] * 100.0 / ((i_mb_count - i_all_intra)*4) );
4423 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "coded y intra: %.1f%%%s\n",
4424 h->stat.i_mb_cbp[0] * 100.0 / (i_all_intra*4), buf );
4425 }
4426
4427 int64_t fixed_pred_modes[4][9] = {{0}};
4428 int64_t sum_pred_modes[4] = {0};
4429 for( int i = 0; i <= I_PRED_16x16_DC_128; i++ )
4430 {
4431 fixed_pred_modes[0][x264_mb_pred_mode16x16_fix[i]] += h->stat.i_mb_pred_mode[0][i];
4432 sum_pred_modes[0] += h->stat.i_mb_pred_mode[0][i];
4433 }
4434 if( sum_pred_modes[0] )
4435 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "i16 v,h,dc,p: %2.0f%% %2.0f%% %2.0f%% %2.0f%%\n",
4436 fixed_pred_modes[0][0] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[0],
4437 fixed_pred_modes[0][1] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[0],
4438 fixed_pred_modes[0][2] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[0],
4439 fixed_pred_modes[0][3] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[0] );
4440 for( int i = 1; i <= 2; i++ )
4441 {
4442 for( int j = 0; j <= I_PRED_8x8_DC_128; j++ )
4443 {
4444 fixed_pred_modes[i][x264_mb_pred_mode4x4_fix(j)] += h->stat.i_mb_pred_mode[i][j];
4445 sum_pred_modes[i] += h->stat.i_mb_pred_mode[i][j];
4446 }
4447 if( sum_pred_modes[i] )
4448 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "i%d v,h,dc,ddl,ddr,vr,hd,vl,hu: %2.0f%% %2.0f%% %2.0f%% %2.0f%% %2.0f%% %2.0f%% %2.0f%% %2.0f%% %2.0f%%\n", (3-i)*4,
4449 fixed_pred_modes[i][0] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[i],
4450 fixed_pred_modes[i][1] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[i],
4451 fixed_pred_modes[i][2] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[i],
4452 fixed_pred_modes[i][3] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[i],
4453 fixed_pred_modes[i][4] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[i],
4454 fixed_pred_modes[i][5] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[i],
4455 fixed_pred_modes[i][6] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[i],
4456 fixed_pred_modes[i][7] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[i],
4457 fixed_pred_modes[i][8] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[i] );
4458 }
4459 for( int i = 0; i <= I_PRED_CHROMA_DC_128; i++ )
4460 {
4461 fixed_pred_modes[3][x264_mb_chroma_pred_mode_fix[i]] += h->stat.i_mb_pred_mode[3][i];
4462 sum_pred_modes[3] += h->stat.i_mb_pred_mode[3][i];
4463 }
4464 if( sum_pred_modes[3] && !CHROMA444 )
4465 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "i8c dc,h,v,p: %2.0f%% %2.0f%% %2.0f%% %2.0f%%\n",
4466 fixed_pred_modes[3][0] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[3],
4467 fixed_pred_modes[3][1] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[3],
4468 fixed_pred_modes[3][2] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[3],
4469 fixed_pred_modes[3][3] * 100.0 / sum_pred_modes[3] );
4470
4471 if( h->param.analyse.i_weighted_pred >= X264_WEIGHTP_SIMPLE && h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_P] > 0 )
4472 {
4473 buf[0] = 0;
4474 if( CHROMA_FORMAT )
4475 sprintf( buf, " UV:%.1f%%", h->stat.i_wpred[1] * 100.0 / h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_P] );
4476 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "Weighted P-Frames: Y:%.1f%%%s\n",
4477 h->stat.i_wpred[0] * 100.0 / h->stat.i_frame_count[SLICE_TYPE_P], buf );
4478 }
4479
4480 for( int i_list = 0; i_list < 2; i_list++ )
4481 for( int i_slice = 0; i_slice < 2; i_slice++ )
4482 {
4483 char *p = buf;
4484 int64_t i_den = 0;
4485 int i_max = 0;
4486 for( int i = 0; i < X264_REF_MAX*2; i++ )
4487 if( h->stat.i_mb_count_ref[i_slice][i_list][i] )
4488 {
4489 i_den += h->stat.i_mb_count_ref[i_slice][i_list][i];
4490 i_max = i;
4491 }
4492 if( i_max == 0 )
4493 continue;
4494 for( int i = 0; i <= i_max; i++ )
4495 p += sprintf( p, " %4.1f%%", 100. * h->stat.i_mb_count_ref[i_slice][i_list][i] / i_den );
4496 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "ref %c L%d:%s\n", "PB"[i_slice], i_list, buf );
4497 }
4498
4499 if( h->param.analyse.b_ssim )
4500 {
4501 float ssim = SUM3( h->stat.f_ssim_mean_y ) / duration;
4502 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "SSIM Mean Y:%.7f (%6.3fdb)\n", ssim, calc_ssim_db( ssim ) );
4503 }
4504 if( h->param.analyse.b_psnr )
4505 {
4506 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO,
4507 "PSNR Mean Y:%6.3f U:%6.3f V:%6.3f Avg:%6.3f Global:%6.3f kb/s:%.2f\n",
4508 SUM3( h->stat.f_psnr_mean_y ) / duration,
4509 SUM3( h->stat.f_psnr_mean_u ) / duration,
4510 SUM3( h->stat.f_psnr_mean_v ) / duration,
4511 SUM3( h->stat.f_psnr_average ) / duration,
4512 calc_psnr( SUM3( h->stat.f_ssd_global ), duration * i_yuv_size ),
4513 f_bitrate );
4514 }
4515 else
4516 x264_log( h, X264_LOG_INFO, "kb/s:%.2f\n", f_bitrate );
4517 }
4518
4519 /* rc */
4520 x264_ratecontrol_delete( h );
4521
4522 /* param */
4523 x264_param_cleanup( &h->param );
4524
4525 x264_cqm_delete( h );
4526 x264_free( h->nal_buffer );
4527 x264_free( h->reconfig_h );
4528 x264_analyse_free_costs( h );
4529 x264_free( h->cost_table );
4530
4531 if( h->i_thread_frames > 1 )
4532 h = h->thread[h->i_thread_phase];
4533
4534 /* frames */
4535 x264_frame_delete_list( h->frames.unused[0] );
4536 x264_frame_delete_list( h->frames.unused[1] );
4537 x264_frame_delete_list( h->frames.current );
4538 x264_frame_delete_list( h->frames.blank_unused );
4539
4540 h = h->thread[0];
4541
4542 for( int i = 0; i < h->i_thread_frames; i++ )
4543 if( h->thread[i]->b_thread_active )
4544 for( int j = 0; j < h->thread[i]->i_ref[0]; j++ )
4545 if( h->thread[i]->fref[0][j] && h->thread[i]->fref[0][j]->b_duplicate )
4546 x264_frame_delete( h->thread[i]->fref[0][j] );
4547
4548 if( h->param.i_lookahead_threads > 1 )
4549 for( int i = 0; i < h->param.i_lookahead_threads; i++ )
4550 x264_free( h->lookahead_thread[i] );
4551
4552 for( int i = h->param.i_threads - 1; i >= 0; i-- )
4553 {
4554 x264_frame_t **frame;
4555
4556 if( !h->param.b_sliced_threads || i == 0 )
4557 {
4558 for( frame = h->thread[i]->frames.reference; *frame; frame++ )
4559 {
4560 assert( (*frame)->i_reference_count > 0 );
4561 (*frame)->i_reference_count--;
4562 if( (*frame)->i_reference_count == 0 )
4563 x264_frame_delete( *frame );
4564 }
4565 frame = &h->thread[i]->fdec;
4566 if( *frame )
4567 {
4568 assert( (*frame)->i_reference_count > 0 );
4569 (*frame)->i_reference_count--;
4570 if( (*frame)->i_reference_count == 0 )
4571 x264_frame_delete( *frame );
4572 }
4573 x264_macroblock_cache_free( h->thread[i] );
4574 }
4575 x264_macroblock_thread_free( h->thread[i], 0 );
4576 x264_free( h->thread[i]->out.p_bitstream );
4577 x264_free( h->thread[i]->out.nal );
4578 x264_pthread_mutex_destroy( &h->thread[i]->mutex );
4579 x264_pthread_cond_destroy( &h->thread[i]->cv );
4580 x264_free( h->thread[i] );
4581 }
4582#if HAVE_OPENCL
4583 x264_opencl_close_library( ocl );
4584#endif
4585}
4586
4587int x264_encoder_delayed_frames( x264_t *h )
4588{
4589 int delayed_frames = 0;
4590 if( h->i_thread_frames > 1 )
4591 {
4592 for( int i = 0; i < h->i_thread_frames; i++ )
4593 delayed_frames += h->thread[i]->b_thread_active;
4594 h = h->thread[h->i_thread_phase];
4595 }
4596 for( int i = 0; h->frames.current[i]; i++ )
4597 delayed_frames++;
4598 x264_pthread_mutex_lock( &h->lookahead->ofbuf.mutex );
4599 x264_pthread_mutex_lock( &h->lookahead->ifbuf.mutex );
4600 x264_pthread_mutex_lock( &h->lookahead->next.mutex );
4601 delayed_frames += h->lookahead->ifbuf.i_size + h->lookahead->next.i_size + h->lookahead->ofbuf.i_size;
4602 x264_pthread_mutex_unlock( &h->lookahead->next.mutex );
4603 x264_pthread_mutex_unlock( &h->lookahead->ifbuf.mutex );
4604 x264_pthread_mutex_unlock( &h->lookahead->ofbuf.mutex );
4605 return delayed_frames;
4606}
